  <Name>k__BackingField: Jeremiah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: jer
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of Jeremiah the son of Hilkiah, of the priests who were 
        in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to whom the word of the Lord came in the days of Josiah the son of
        Amon, king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Prophet Is Called'
      title: The Prophet Is Called
      number: 3
      content: It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah,
        until the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah the son of Josiah, king of
        Judah, until the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBefore I formed you in the womb I knew you;Before you were
        born I sanctified you;I ordained you a prophet to the nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then said I:\u201CAh, Lord God!Behold, I cannot speak, for I am a
        youth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Lord said to me:\u201CDo not say, \u2018I am a youth,\u2019For
        you shall go to all to whom I send you,And whatever I command you, you shall
        speak."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Do not be afraid of their faces,For I am with you to deliver you,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord put forth His hand and touched my mouth, and the Lord
        said to me:\u201CBehold, I have put My words in your mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "See, I have this day set you over the nations and over the kingdoms,To
        root out and to pull down,To destroy and to throw down,To build and to plant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying, \u201CJeremiah,
        what do you see?\u201DAnd I said, \u201CI see a branch of an almond tree.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CYou have seen well, for I am ready
        to perform My word.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the word of the Lord came to me the second time, saying, \u201CWhat
        do you see?\u201DAnd I said, \u201CI see a boiling pot, and it is facing
        away from the north.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to me:\u201COut of the north calamity shall break
        forthOn all the inhabitants of the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For behold, I am callingAll the families of the kingdoms of the north,\u201D
        says the Lord;\u201CThey shall come and each one set his throneAt the entrance
        of the gates of Jerusalem,Against all its walls all around,And against all
        the cities of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I will utter My judgmentsAgainst them concerning all their wickedness,Because
        they have forsaken Me,Burned incense to other gods,And worshiped the works
        of their own hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore prepare yourself and arise,And speak to them all
        that I command you.Do not be dismayed before their faces,Lest I dismay you
        before them."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For behold, I have made you this dayA fortified city and an iron
        pillar,And bronze walls against the whole land\u2014Against the kings of
        Judah,Against its princes,Against its priests,And against the people of the
        land."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They will fight against you,But they shall not prevail against you.For
        I am with you,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cto deliver you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Case Against Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Case Against Israel"
      number: 1
      content: Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo and cry in the hearing of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord:\u201CI remember you,The kindness of your youth,The love of
        your betrothal,When you went after Me in the wilderness,In a land not sown."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Israel was holiness to the Lord,The firstfruits of His increase.All
        that devour him will offend;Disaster will come upon them,\u201D says the
        Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear the word of the Lord, O house of Jacob and all the families
        of the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CWhat injustice have your fathers found in
        Me,That they have gone far from Me,Have followed idols,And have become idolaters?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Neither did they say, \u2018Where is the Lord,Who brought us up out
        of the land of Egypt,Who led us through the wilderness,Through a land of
        deserts and pits,Through a land of drought and the shadow of death,Through
        a land that no one crossedAnd where no one dwelt?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I brought you into a bountiful country,To eat its fruit and its goodness.But
        when you entered, you defiled My landAnd made My heritage an abomination.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The priests did not say, \u2018Where is the Lord?\u2019And those
        who handle the law did not know Me;The rulers also transgressed against Me;The
        prophets prophesied by Baal,And walked after things  that do not profit."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will yet bring charges against you,\u201D says
        the Lord,\u201CAnd against your children\u2019s children I will bring charges."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For pass beyond the coasts of Cyprus and see,Send to Kedar and consider
        diligently,And see if there has been such a  thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Has a nation changed its gods,Which are  not gods?But My people have
        changed their GloryFor what does not profit.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Be astonished, O heavens, at this,And be horribly afraid;Be very
        desolate,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor My people have committed two evils:They have forsaken Me,
        the fountain of living waters,And hewn themselves cisterns\u2014broken cisterns
        that can hold no water."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIs Israel a servant?Is he a homeborn slave?Why is he plundered?"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The young lions roared at him, and growled;They made his land waste;His
        cities are burned, without inhabitant.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Also the people of Noph and TahpanhesHave broken the crown of your
        head.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Have you not brought this on yourself,In that you have forsaken the
        Lord your GodWhen He led you in the way?
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And now why take the road to Egypt,To drink the waters of Sihor?Or
        why take the road to Assyria,To drink the waters of the River?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your own wickedness will correct you,And your backslidings will rebuke
        you.Know therefore and see that it  is an evil and bitter thingThat you have
        forsaken the Lord your God,And the fear of Me is not in you,\u201DSays the
        Lord God of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor of old I have broken your yoke and burst your bonds;And
        you said, \u2018I will not transgress,\u2019When on every high hill and under
        every green treeYou lay down, playing the harlot."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Yet I had planted you a noble vine, a seed of highest quality.How
        then have you turned before MeInto the degenerate plant of an alien vine?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For though you wash yourself with lye, and use much soap,Yet your
        iniquity is marked before Me,\u201D says the Lord God."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018I am not polluted,I have not gone after
        the Baals\u2019?See your way in the valley;Know what you have done:You  are
        a swift dromedary breaking loose in her ways,"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: A wild donkey used to the wilderness,That sniffs at the wind in her
        desire;In her time of mating, who can turn her away?All those who seek her
        will not weary themselves;In her month they will find her.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Withhold your foot from being unshod, and your throat from thirst.But
        you said, \u2018There is no hope.No! For I have loved aliens, and after them
        I will go.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAs the thief is ashamed when he is found out,So is the house
        of Israel ashamed;They and their kings and their princes, and their priests
        and their prophets,"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Saying to a tree, \u2018You are my father,\u2019And to a stone, \u2018You
        gave birth to me.\u2019For they have turned their back to Me, and not their
        face.But in the time of their troubleThey will say, \u2018Arise and save
        us.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: But where are your gods that you have made for yourselves?Let them
        arise,If they can save you in the time of your trouble;For according  to
        the number of your citiesAre your gods, O Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhy will you plead with Me?You all have transgressed against
        Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CIn vain I have chastened your children;They received no correction.Your
        sword has devoured your prophetsLike a destroying lion."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CO generation, see the word of the Lord!Have I been a wilderness
        to Israel,Or a land of darkness?Why do My people say, \u2018We are lords;We
        will come no more to You\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Can a virgin forget her ornaments,Or a bride her attire?Yet My people
        have forgotten Me days without number.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CWhy do you beautify your way to seek love?Therefore you have
        also taughtThe wicked women your ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Also on your skirts is foundThe blood of the lives of the poor innocents.I
        have not found it by secret search,But plainly on all these things.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Yet you say, \u2018Because I am innocent,Surely His anger shall turn
        from me.\u2019Behold, I will plead My case against you,Because you say, \u2018I
        have not sinned.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Why do you gad about so much to change your way?Also you shall be
        ashamed of Egypt as you were ashamed of Assyria.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Indeed you will go forth from himWith your hands on your head;For
        the Lord has rejected your trusted allies,And you will not prosper by them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Is Shameless'
      title: Israel Is Shameless
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThey say, \u2018If a man divorces his wife,And she goes from
        himAnd becomes another man\u2019s,May he return to her again?\u2019Would
        not that land be greatly polluted?But you have played the harlot with many
        lovers;Yet return to Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes to the desolate heights and see:Where have
        you not lain with  men?By the road you have sat for themLike an Arabian in
        the wilderness;And you have polluted the landWith your harlotries and your
        wickedness."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore the showers have been withheld,And there has been no latter
        rain.You have had a harlot\u2019s forehead;You refuse to be ashamed."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Will you not from this time cry to Me,\u2018My Father, You are  the
        guide of my youth?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 5
      content: "Will He remain angry forever?Will He keep it to the end?\u2019Behold,
        you have spoken and done evil things,As you were able.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The Lord said also to me in the days of Josiah the king: \u201CHave
        you seen what backsliding Israel has done? She has gone up on every high
        mountain and under every green tree, and there played the harlot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I said, after she had done all these things, \u2018Return to
        Me.\u2019 But she did not return. And her treacherous sister Judah saw it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I saw that for all the causes for which backsliding Israel had
        committed adultery, I had put her away and given her a certificate of divorce;
        yet her treacherous sister Judah did not fear, but went and played the harlot
        also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So it came to pass, through her casual harlotry, that she defiled
        the land and committed adultery with stones and trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And yet for all this her treacherous sister Judah has not turned
        to Me with her whole heart, but in pretense,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CBacksliding Israel has shown herself
        more righteous than treacherous Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Go and proclaim these words toward the north, and say:\u2018Return,
        backsliding Israel,\u2019 says the Lord;\u2018I will not cause My anger to
        fall on you.For I am  merciful,\u2019 says the Lord;\u2018I will not remain
        angry forever."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Only acknowledge your iniquity,That you have transgressed against
        the Lord your God,And have scattered your charmsTo alien deities under every
        green tree,And you have not obeyed My voice,\u2019 says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CReturn, O backsliding children,\u201D says the Lord; \u201Cfor
        I am married to you. I will take you, one from a city and two from a family,
        and I will bring you to Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And I will give you shepherds according to My heart, who will feed
        you with knowledge and understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThen it shall come to pass, when you are multiplied and increased
        in the land in those days,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat they will say
        no more, \u2018The ark of the covenant of the Lord.\u2019 It shall not come
        to mind, nor shall they remember it, nor shall they visit it, nor shall it
        be made anymore."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAt that time Jerusalem shall be called The Throne of the Lord,
        and all the nations shall be gathered to it, to the name of the Lord, to
        Jerusalem. No more shall they follow the dictates of their evil hearts."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIn those days the house of Judah shall walk with the house
        of Israel, and they shall come together out of the land of the north to the
        land that I have given as an inheritance to your fathers."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBut I said:\u2018How can I put you among the childrenAnd give
        you a pleasant land,A beautiful heritage of the hosts of nations?\u2019\u201CAnd
        I said:\u2018You shall call Me, \u201CMy Father,\u201DAnd not turn away from
        Me.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Surely, as a wife treacherously departs from her husband,So have
        you dealt treacherously with Me,O house of Israel,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: A voice was heard on the desolate heights,Weeping and supplications
        of the children of Israel.For they have perverted their way;They have forgotten
        the Lord their God.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CReturn, you backsliding children,And I will heal your backslidings.\u201D\u201CIndeed
        we do come to You,For You are the Lord our God."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Truly, in vain is  salvation  hoped  for from the hills,And  from
        the multitude of mountains;Truly, in the Lord our GodIs the salvation of
        Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For shame has devouredThe labor of our fathers from our youth\u2014Their
        flocks and their herds,Their sons and their daughters."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "We lie down in our shame,And our reproach covers us.For we have sinned
        against the Lord our God,We and our fathers,From our youth even to this day,And
        have not obeyed the voice of the Lord our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CIf you will return, O Israel,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CReturn
        to Me;And if you will put away your abominations out of My sight,Then you
        shall not be moved."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you shall swear, \u2018The Lord lives,\u2019In truth, in judgment,
        and in righteousness;The nations shall bless themselves in Him,And in Him
        they shall glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the Lord to the men of Judah and Jerusalem:\u201CBreak
        up your fallow ground,And do not sow among thorns."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: An Imminent Invasion'
      title: An Imminent Invasion
      number: 4
      content: "Circumcise yourselves to the Lord,And take away the foreskins of
        your hearts,You men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem,Lest My fury come
        forth like fire,And burn so that no one can quench it,Because of the evil
        of your doings.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Declare in Judah and proclaim in Jerusalem, and say:\u201CBlow the
        trumpet in the land;Cry, \u2018Gather together,\u2019And say, \u2018Assemble
        yourselves,And let us go into the fortified cities.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Set up the standard toward Zion.Take refuge! Do not delay!For I will
        bring disaster from the north,And great destruction.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The lion has come up from his thicket,And the destroyer of nations
        is on his way.He has gone forth from his placeTo make your land desolate.Your
        cities will be laid waste,Without inhabitant.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For this, clothe yourself with sackcloth,Lament and wail.For the fierce
        anger of the LordHas not turned back from us.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall come to pass in that day,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat
        the heart of the king shall perish,And the heart of the princes;The priests
        shall be astonished,And the prophets shall wonder.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord God!Surely You have greatly deceived
        this people and Jerusalem,Saying, \u2018You shall have peace,\u2019Whereas
        the sword reaches to the heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "At that time it will be saidTo this people and to Jerusalem,\u201CA
        dry wind of the desolate heights blows in the wildernessToward the daughter
        of My people\u2014Not to fan or to cleanse\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "A wind too strong for these will come for Me;Now I will also speak
        judgment against them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, he shall come up like clouds,And his chariots like
        a whirlwind.His horses are swifter than eagles.Woe to us, for we are plundered!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: O Jerusalem, wash your heart from wickedness,That you may be saved.How
        long shall your evil thoughts lodge within you?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For a voice declares from DanAnd proclaims affliction from Mount
        Ephraim:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CMake mention to the nations,Yes, proclaim against Jerusalem,That
        watchers come from a far countryAnd raise their voice against the cities
        of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Like keepers of a field they are against her all around,Because she
        has been rebellious against Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Sorrow for the Doomed Nation'
      title: Sorrow for the Doomed Nation
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYour ways and your doingsHave procured these things for you.This
        is your wickedness,Because it is bitter,Because it reaches to your heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: O my soul, my soul!I am pained in my very heart!My heart makes a noise
        in me;I cannot hold my peace,Because you have heard, O my soul,The sound
        of the trumpet,The alarm of war.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Destruction upon destruction is cried,For the whole land is plundered.Suddenly
        my tents are plundered,And my curtains in a moment.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: How long will I see the standard,And hear the sound of the trumpet?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor My people are foolish,They have not known Me.They are silly
        children,And they have no understanding.They are wise to do evil,But to do
        good they have no knowledge.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: I beheld the earth, and indeed it  was  without form, and void;And
        the heavens, they had no light.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: I beheld the mountains, and indeed they trembled,And all the hills
        moved back and forth.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: I beheld, and indeed there  was no man,And all the birds of the heavens
        had fled.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: I beheld, and indeed the fruitful land was a wilderness,And all its
        cities were broken downAt the presence of the Lord,By His fierce anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CThe whole land shall be desolate;Yet
        I will not make a full end."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: For this shall the earth mourn,And the heavens above be black,Because
        I have spoken.I have purposed and will not relent,Nor will I turn back from
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The whole city shall flee from the noise of the horsemen and bowmen.They
        shall go into thickets and climb up on the rocks.Every city shall  be forsaken,And
        not a man shall dwell in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAnd when you are plundered,What will you do?Though you clothe
        yourself with crimson,Though you adorn yourself with ornaments of gold,Though
        you enlarge your eyes with paint,In vain you will make yourself fair;Your
        lovers will despise you;They will seek your life."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFor I have heard a voice as of a woman in labor,The anguish
        as of her who brings forth her first child,The voice of the daughter of Zion
        bewailing herself;She spreads her hands, saying,\u2018Woe is me now, for
        my soul is wearyBecause of murderers!\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Justice of God\u2019s Judgment"
      title: "The Justice of God\u2019s Judgment"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CRun to and fro through the streets of Jerusalem;See now and
        know;And seek in her open placesIf you can find a man,If there is anyone
        who executes judgment,Who seeks the truth,And I will pardon her."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Though they say, \u2018As  the Lord lives,\u2019Surely they swear
        falsely.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: O Lord, are not Your eyes on the truth?You have stricken them,But
        they have not grieved;You have consumed them,But they have refused to receive
        correction.They have made their faces harder than rock;They have refused
        to return.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore I said, \u201CSurely these are poor.They are foolish;For
        they do not know the way of the Lord,The judgment of their God."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I will go to the great men and speak to them,For they have known
        the way of the Lord,The judgment of their God.\u201DBut these have altogether
        broken the yokeAnd burst the bonds."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Therefore a lion from the forest shall slay them,A wolf of the deserts
        shall destroy them;A leopard will watch over their cities.Everyone who goes
        out from there shall be torn in pieces,Because their transgressions are many;Their
        backslidings have increased.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHow shall I pardon you for this?Your children have forsaken
        MeAnd sworn by those  that are not gods.When I had fed them to the full,Then
        they committed adulteryAnd assembled themselves by troops in the harlots\u2019
        houses."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They were like well-fed lusty stallions;Every one neighed after his
        neighbor\u2019s wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I not punish them for these things?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CAnd
        shall I not avenge Myself on such a nation as this?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo up on her walls and destroy,But do not make a complete end.Take
        away her branches,For they are not the Lord\u2019s."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the house of Israel and the house of JudahHave dealt very treacherously
        with Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They have lied about the Lord,And said, \u201CIt  is not He.Neither
        will evil come upon us,Nor shall we see sword or famine."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the prophets become wind,For the word is not in them.Thus shall
        it be done to them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God of hosts:\u201CBecause you speak
        this word,Behold, I will make My words in your mouth fire,And this people
        wood,And it shall devour them."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Behold, I will bring a nation against you from afar,O house of Israel,\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CIt is a mighty nation,It is an ancient nation,A nation
        whose language you do not know,Nor can you understand what they say."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Their quiver is like an open tomb;They are all mighty men.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And they shall eat up your harvest and your bread,Which your sons
        and daughters should eat.They shall eat up your flocks and your herds;They
        shall eat up your vines and your fig trees;They shall destroy your fortified
        cities,In which you trust, with the sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CNevertheless in those days,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will
        not make a complete end of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And it will be when you say, \u2018Why does the Lord our God do all
        these things to us?\u2019 then you shall answer them, \u2018Just as you have
        forsaken Me and served foreign gods in your land, so you shall serve aliens
        in a land that  is not yours.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CDeclare this in the house of JacobAnd proclaim it in Judah,
        saying,"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Hear this now, O foolish people,Without understanding,Who have
        eyes and see not,And who have ears and hear not:"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do you not fear Me?\u2019 says the Lord.\u2018Will you not tremble
        at My presence,Who have placed the sand as the bound of the sea,By a perpetual
        decree, that it cannot pass beyond it?And though its waves toss to and fro,Yet
        they cannot prevail;Though they roar, yet they cannot pass over it."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But this people has a defiant and rebellious heart;They have revolted
        and departed.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They do not say in their heart,\u201CLet us now fear the Lord our
        God,Who gives rain, both the former and the latter, in its season.He reserves
        for us the appointed weeks of the harvest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Your iniquities have turned these things away,And your sins have withheld
        good from you.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018For among My people are found wicked men;They lie in wait as
        one who sets snares;They set a trap;They catch men."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: As a cage is full of birds,So their houses are full of deceit.Therefore
        they have become great and grown rich.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: They have grown fat, they are sleek;Yes, they surpass the deeds of
        the wicked;They do not plead the cause,The cause of the fatherless;Yet they
        prosper,And the right of the needy they do not defend.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Shall I not punish them for these things?\u2019 says the Lord.\u2018Shall
        I not avenge Myself on such a nation as this?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAn astonishing and horrible thingHas been committed in the
        land:"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The prophets prophesy falsely,And the priests rule by their own power;And
        My people love to  have  it so.But what will you do in the end?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Impending Destruction from the North'
      title: Impending Destruction from the North
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CO you children of Benjamin,Gather yourselves to flee from the
        midst of Jerusalem!Blow the trumpet in Tekoa,And set up a signal-fire in
        Beth Haccerem;For disaster appears out of the north,And great destruction."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: I have likened the daughter of ZionTo a lovely and delicate woman.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The shepherds with their flocks shall come to her.They shall pitch
        their tents against her all around.Each one shall pasture in his own place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CPrepare war against her;Arise, and let us go up at noon.Woe
        to us, for the day goes away,For the shadows of the evening are lengthening."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Arise, and let us go by night,And let us destroy her palaces.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus has the Lord of hosts said:\u201CCut down trees,And build
        a mound against Jerusalem.This is the city to be punished.She is full of
        oppression in her midst."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: As a fountain wells up with water,So she wells up with her wickedness.Violence
        and plundering are heard in her.Before Me continually are grief and wounds.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Be instructed, O Jerusalem,Lest My soul depart from you;Lest I make
        you desolate,A land not inhabited.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CThey shall thoroughly glean as
        a vine the remnant of Israel;As a grape-gatherer, put your hand back into
        the branches.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: To whom shall I speak and give warning,That they may hear?Indeed their
        ear is uncircumcised,And they cannot give heed.Behold, the word of the Lord
        is a reproach to them;They have no delight in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore I am full of the fury of the Lord.I am weary of holding
        it in.\u201CI will pour it out on the children outside,And on the assembly
        of young men together;For even the husband shall be taken with the wife,The
        aged with him  who  is full of days."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And their houses shall be turned over to others,Fields and wives
        together;For I will stretch out My handAgainst the inhabitants of the land,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBecause from the least of them even to the greatest of them,Everyone
        is given to covetousness;And from the prophet even to the priest,Everyone
        deals falsely."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They have also healed the hurt of My people slightly,Saying, \u2018Peace,
        peace!\u2019When there  is no peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination?No! They were
        not at all ashamed;Nor did they know how to blush.Therefore they shall fall
        among those who fall;At the time I punish them,They shall be cast down,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CStand in the ways and see,And ask for the
        old paths, where the good way is,And walk in it;Then you will find rest for
        your souls.But they said, \u2018We will not walk in  it.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Also, I set watchmen over you, saying,\u2018Listen to the sound of
        the trumpet!\u2019But they said, \u2018We will not listen.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Therefore hear, you nations,And know, O congregation, what is among
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Hear, O earth!Behold, I will certainly bring calamity on this people\u2014The
        fruit of their thoughts,Because they have not heeded My wordsNor My law,
        but rejected it."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For what purpose to MeComes frankincense from Sheba,And sweet cane
        from a far country?Your burnt offerings are not acceptable,Nor your sacrifices
        sweet to Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I will lay stumbling blocks
        before this people,And the fathers and the sons together shall fall on them.The
        neighbor and his friend shall perish.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, a people comes from the north country,And
        a great nation will be raised from the farthest parts of the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They will lay hold on bow and spear;They are cruel and have no mercy;Their
        voice roars like the sea;And they ride on horses,As men of war set in array
        against you, O daughter of Zion.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: We have heard the report of it;Our hands grow feeble.Anguish has taken
        hold of us,Pain as of a woman in labor.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Do not go out into the field,Nor walk by the way.Because of the sword
        of the enemy,Fear is on every side.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: O daughter of my people,Dress in sackclothAnd roll about in ashes!Make
        mourning as  for an only son, most bitter lamentation;For the plunderer will
        suddenly come upon us.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI have set you as an assayer and  a fortress among My people,That
        you may know and test their way."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: They are all stubborn rebels, walking as slanderers.They  are  bronze
        and iron,They are all corrupters;
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The bellows blow fiercely,The lead is consumed by the fire;The smelter
        refines in vain,For the wicked are not drawn off.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "People will call them rejected silver,Because the Lord has rejected
        them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Trusting in Lying Words'
      title: Trusting in Lying Words
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CStand in the gate of the Lord\u2019s house, and proclaim there
        this word, and say, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, all you  of Judah who
        enter in at these gates to worship the Lord!\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CAmend your
        ways and your doings, and I will cause you to dwell in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not trust in these lying words, saying, \u2018The temple of the
        Lord, the temple of the Lord, the temple of the Lord  are these.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor if you thoroughly amend your ways and your doings, if you
        thoroughly execute judgment between a man and his neighbor, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'if you do not oppress the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow,
        and do not shed innocent blood in this place, or walk after other gods to
        your hurt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: then I will cause you to dwell in this place, in the land that I gave
        to your fathers forever and ever.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, you trust in lying words that cannot profit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will you steal, murder, commit adultery, swear falsely, burn incense
        to Baal, and walk after other gods whom you do not know, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and then come and stand before Me in this house which is called by
        My name, and say, \u2018We are delivered to do all these abominations\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Has this house, which is called by My name, become a den of thieves
        in your eyes? Behold, I, even I, have seen it,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut go now to My place which was in Shiloh, where I set My
        name at the first, and see what I did to it because of the wickedness of
        My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And now, because you have done all these works,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cand I spoke to you, rising up early and speaking, but you did not hear,
        and I called you, but you did not answer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'therefore I will do to the house which is called by My name, in which
        you trust, and to this place which I gave to you and your fathers, as I have
        done to Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And I will cast you out of My sight, as I have cast out all your
        brethren\u2014the whole posterity of Ephraim."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTherefore do not pray for this people, nor lift up a cry or
        prayer for them, nor make intercession to Me; for I will not hear you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do you not see what they do in the cities of Judah and in the streets
        of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The children gather wood, the fathers kindle the fire, and the women
        knead dough, to make cakes for the queen of heaven; and they  pour out drink
        offerings to other gods, that they may provoke Me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Do they provoke Me to anger?\u201D says the Lord. \u201CDo  they
        not provoke themselves, to the shame of their own faces?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God: \u201CBehold, My anger and My fury
        will be poured out on this place\u2014on man and on beast, on the trees of
        the field and on the fruit of the ground. And it will burn and not be quenched.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CAdd your burnt
        offerings to your sacrifices and eat meat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I did not speak to your fathers, or command them in the day that
        I brought them out of the land of Egypt, concerning burnt offerings or sacrifices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But this is what I commanded them, saying, \u2018Obey My voice, and
        I will be your God, and you shall be My people. And walk in all the ways
        that I have commanded you, that it may be well with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yet they did not obey or incline their ear, but followed the counsels
        and the dictates of their evil hearts, and went backward and not forward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Since the day that your fathers came out of the land of Egypt until
        this day, I have even sent to you all My servants the prophets, daily rising
        up early and sending them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Yet they did not obey Me or incline their ear, but stiffened their
        neck. They did worse than their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Judgment on Obscene Religion'
      title: Judgment on Obscene Religion
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CTherefore you shall speak all these words to them, but they
        will not obey you. You shall also call to them, but they will not answer
        you."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CSo you shall say to them, \u2018This is a nation that does
        not obey the voice of the Lord their God nor receive correction. Truth has
        perished and has been cut off from their mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Cut off your hair and cast it away, and take up a lamentation on
        the desolate heights; for the Lord has rejected and forsaken the generation
        of His wrath.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For the children of Judah have done evil in My sight,\u201D says
        the Lord. \u201CThey have set their abominations in the house which is called
        by My name, to pollute it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And they have built the high places of Tophet, which is in the Valley
        of the Son of Hinnom, to burn their sons and their daughters in the fire,
        which I did not command, nor did it come into My heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cwhen it will no more be called Tophet, or the Valley of the Son of
        Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter; for they will bury in Tophet until there
        is no room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The corpses of this people will be food for the birds of the heaven
        and for the beasts of the earth. And no one will frighten them  away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Then I will cause to cease from the cities of Judah and from the streets
        of Jerusalem the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the
        bridegroom and the voice of the bride. For the land shall be desolate.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAt that time,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthey shall bring out
        the bones of the kings of Judah, and the bones of its princes, and the bones
        of the priests, and the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, out of their graves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They shall spread them before the sun and the moon and all the host
        of heaven, which they have loved and which they have served and after which
        they have walked, which they have sought and which they have worshiped. They
        shall not be gathered nor buried; they shall be like refuse on the face of
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Peril of False Teaching'
      title: The Peril of False Teaching
      number: 3
      content: "Then death shall be chosen rather than life by all the residue of
        those who remain of this evil family, who remain in all the places where
        I have driven them,\u201D says the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CMoreover you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord:\u201CWill
        they fall and not rise?Will one turn away and not return?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Why has this people slidden back,Jerusalem, in a perpetual backsliding?They
        hold fast to deceit,They refuse to return.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I listened and heard,But they do not speak aright.No man repented
        of his wickedness,Saying, \u2018What have I done?\u2019Everyone turned to
        his own course,As the horse rushes into the battle."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CEven the stork in the heavensKnows her appointed times;And
        the turtledove, the swift, and the swallowObserve the time of their coming.But
        My people do not know the judgment of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018We are wise,And the law of the Lord 
        is with us\u2019?Look, the false pen of the scribe certainly works falsehood."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The wise men are ashamed,They are dismayed and taken.Behold, they
        have rejected the word of the Lord;So what wisdom do they have?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Therefore I will give their wives to others,And their fields to those
        who will inherit them;Because from the least even to the greatestEveryone
        is given to covetousness;From the prophet even to the priestEveryone deals
        falsely.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For they have healed the hurt of the daughter of My people slightly,Saying,
        \u2018Peace, peace!\u2019When there  is no peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Were they ashamed when they had committed abomination?No! They were
        not at all ashamed,Nor did they know how to blush.Therefore they shall fall
        among those who fall;In the time of their punishmentThey shall be cast down,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI will surely consume them,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CNo grapes
        shall  be  on the vine,Nor figs on the fig tree,And the leaf shall fade;And
        the  things I have given them shall pass away from them.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhy do we sit still?Assemble yourselves,And let us enter the
        fortified cities,And let us be silent there.For the Lord our God has put
        us to silenceAnd given us water of gall to drink,Because we have sinned against
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWe  looked for peace, but no good came;And for a time of health,
        and there was trouble!"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The snorting of His horses was heard from Dan.The whole land trembled
        at the sound of the neighing of His strong ones;For they have come and devoured
        the land and all that is in it,The city and those who dwell in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Prophet Mourns for the People'
      title: The Prophet Mourns for the People
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor behold, I will send serpents among you,Vipers which cannot
        be charmed,And they shall bite you,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: I would comfort myself in sorrow;My heart is faint in me.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Listen! The voice,The cry of the daughter of my peopleFrom a far
        country:\u201CIs not the Lord in Zion?Is not her King in her?\u201D\u201CWhy
        have they provoked Me to angerWith their carved images\u2014With foreign
        idols?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe harvest is past,The summer is ended,And we are not saved!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For the hurt of the daughter of my people I am hurt.I am mourning;Astonishment
        has taken hold of me.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Is  there no balm in Gilead,Is  there no physician there?Why then
        is there no recoveryFor the health of the daughter of my people?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Oh, that my head were waters,And my eyes a fountain of tears,That
        I might weep day and nightFor the slain of the daughter of my people!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Oh, that I had in the wildernessA lodging place for travelers;That
        I might leave my people,And go from them!For they are all adulterers,An assembly
        of treacherous men.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd like their bow they have bent their tongues for lies.They
        are not valiant for the truth on the earth.For they proceed from evil to
        evil,And they do not know Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CEveryone take heed to his neighbor,And do not trust any brother;For
        every brother will utterly supplant,And every neighbor will walk with slanderers."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Everyone will deceive his neighbor,And will not speak the truth;They
        have taught their tongue to speak lies;They weary themselves to commit iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Your dwelling place is in the midst of deceit;Through deceit they
        refuse to know Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CBehold, I will refine
        them and try them;For how shall I deal with the daughter of My people?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Their tongue is an arrow shot out;It speaks deceit;One speaks peaceably
        to his neighbor with his mouth,But in his heart he lies in wait.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I not punish them for these things?\u201D says the Lord.\u201CShall
        I not avenge Myself on such a nation as this?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I will take up a weeping and wailing for the mountains,And for the
        dwelling places of the wilderness a lamentation,Because they are burned up,So
        that no one can pass through;Nor can men hear the voice of the cattle.Both
        the birds of the heavens and the beasts have fled;They are gone.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI will make Jerusalem a heap of ruins, a den of jackals.I will
        make the cities of Judah desolate, without an inhabitant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Who is the wise man who may understand this? And who  is  he to whom
        the mouth of the Lord has spoken, that he may declare it? Why does the land
        perish and burn up like a wilderness, so that no one can pass through?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CBecause they have forsaken My law which
        I set before them, and have not obeyed My voice, nor walked according to
        it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "but they have walked according to the dictates of their own hearts
        and after the Baals, which their fathers taught them,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CBehold,
        I will feed them, this people, with wormwood, and give them water of gall
        to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The People Mourn in Judgment'
      title: The People Mourn in Judgment
      number: 16
      content: "I will scatter them also among the Gentiles, whom neither they nor
        their fathers have known. And I will send a sword after them until I have
        consumed them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CConsider and call for the mourning
        women,That they may come;And send for skillful wailing women,That they may
        come."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Let them make hasteAnd take up a wailing for us,That our eyes may
        run with tears,And our eyelids gush with water.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For a voice of wailing is heard from Zion:\u2018How we are plundered!We
        are greatly ashamed,Because we have forsaken the land,Because we have been
        cast out of our dwellings.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Yet hear the word of the Lord, O women,And let your ear receive the
        word of His mouth;Teach your daughters wailing,And everyone her neighbor
        a lamentation.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For death has come through our windows,Has entered our palaces,To
        kill off the children\u2014 no  longer  to  be outside!And the young men\u2014
        no  longer on the streets!"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Speak, \u201CThus says the Lord:\u2018Even the carcasses of men shall
        fall as refuse on the open field,Like cuttings after the harvester,And no
        one shall gather them.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CLet not the wise man glory in his wisdom,Let
        not the mighty man glory in his might,Nor let the rich man glory in his riches;"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But let him who glories glory in this,That he understands and knows
        Me,That I am the Lord, exercising lovingkindness, judgment, and righteousness
        in the earth.For in these I delight,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat
        I will punish all who  are circumcised with the uncircumcised\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Egypt, Judah, Edom, the people of Ammon, Moab, and all who  are in
        the farthest corners, who dwell in the wilderness. For all these nations
        are uncircumcised, and all the house of Israel are  uncircumcised in the
        heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idols and the True God'
      title: Idols and the True God
      number: 1
      content: Hear the word which the Lord speaks to you, O house of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CDo not learn the way of the Gentiles;Do
        not be dismayed at the signs of heaven,For the Gentiles are dismayed at them."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the customs of the peoples are futile;For one cuts a tree from
        the forest,The work of the hands of the workman, with the ax.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They decorate it with silver and gold;They fasten it with nails and
        hammersSo that it will not topple.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They are upright, like a palm tree,And they cannot speak;They must
        be carried,Because they cannot go by  themselves.Do not be afraid of them,For
        they cannot do evil,Nor can they do any good.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Inasmuch as there  is none like You, O Lord(You are great, and Your
        name is great in might),
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Who would not fear You, O King of the nations?For this is Your rightful
        due.For among all the wise men of the nations,And in all their kingdoms,There 
        is none like You.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: But they are altogether dull-hearted and foolish;A wooden idol is
        a worthless doctrine.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Silver is beaten into plates;It is brought from Tarshish,And gold
        from Uphaz,The work of the craftsmanAnd of the hands of the metalsmith;Blue
        and purple are their clothing;They are all the work of skillful men.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But the Lord  is the true God;He is  the living God and the everlasting
        King.At His wrath the earth will tremble,And the nations will not be able
        to endure His indignation.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus you shall say to them: \u201CThe gods that have not made the
        heavens and the earth shall perish from the earth and from under these heavens.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He has made the earth by His power,He has established the world by
        His wisdom,And has stretched out the heavens at His discretion.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When He utters His voice,There  is a multitude of waters in the heavens:\u201CAnd
        He causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth.He makes lightning
        for the rain,He brings the wind out of His treasuries.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Everyone is dull-hearted, without knowledge;Every metalsmith is put
        to shame by an image;For his molded image is falsehood,And there  is no breath
        in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They are futile, a work of errors;In the time of their punishment
        they shall perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Coming Captivity of Judah'
      title: The Coming Captivity of Judah
      number: 16
      content: The Portion of Jacob is not like them,For He is the Maker of all things,And
        Israel is the tribe of His inheritance;The Lord of hosts is His name.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Gather up your wares from the land,O inhabitant of the fortress!
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I will throw out at this timeThe
        inhabitants of the land,And will distress them,That they may find it  so.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Woe is me for my hurt!My wound is severe.But I say, \u201CTruly this
        is an infirmity,And I must bear it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: My tent is plundered,And all my cords are broken;My children have
        gone from me,And they are  no more.There  is no one to pitch my tent anymore,Or
        set up my curtains.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For the shepherds have become dull-hearted,And have not sought the
        Lord;Therefore they shall not prosper,And all their flocks shall be scattered.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Behold, the noise of the report has come,And a great commotion out
        of the north country,To make the cities of Judah desolate, a den of jackals.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: O Lord, I know the way of man is not in himself;It  is not in man
        who walks to direct his own steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: O Lord, correct me, but with justice;Not in Your anger, lest You bring
        me to nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Pour out Your fury on the Gentiles, who do not know You,And on the
        families who do not call on Your name;For they have eaten up Jacob,Devoured
        him and consumed him,And made his dwelling place desolate.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Covenant'
      title: The Broken Covenant
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear the words of this covenant, and speak to the men of Judah
        and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel: \u201CCursed
        is the man who does not obey the words of this covenant "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "which I commanded your fathers in the day I brought them out of the
        land of Egypt, from the iron furnace, saying, \u2018Obey My voice, and do
        according to all that I command you; so shall you be My people, and I will
        be your God,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "that I may establish the oath which I have sworn to your fathers,
        to give them \u2018a land flowing with milk and honey,\u2019 as it  is this
        day.\u201D \u2019 \u201DAnd I answered and said, \u201CSo be it, Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CProclaim all these words in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, saying: \u2018Hear the words of
        this covenant and do them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For I earnestly exhorted your fathers in the day I brought them up
        out of the land of Egypt, until this day, rising early and exhorting, saying,
        \u201CObey My voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yet they did not obey or incline their ear, but everyone followed
        the dictates of his evil heart; therefore I will bring upon them all the
        words of this covenant, which I commanded them to do, but which they have
        not done.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CA conspiracy has been found among
        the men of Judah and among the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have turned back to the iniquities of their forefathers who
        refused to hear My words, and they have gone after other gods to serve them;
        the house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken My covenant which
        I made with their fathers.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, I will surely bring calamity
        on them which they will not be able to escape; and though they cry out to
        Me, I will not listen to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the cities of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem will go
        and cry out to the gods to whom they offer incense, but they will not save
        them at all in the time of their trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For according  to the number of your cities were your gods, O Judah;
        and according  to the number of the streets of Jerusalem you have set up
        altars to that shameful thing, altars to burn incense to Baal.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CSo do not pray for this people, or lift up a cry or prayer
        for them; for I will not hear them in the time that they cry out to Me because
        of their trouble."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhat has My beloved to do in My house,Having done lewd deeds
        with many?And the holy flesh has passed from you.When you do evil, then you
        rejoice."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The Lord called your name,Green Olive Tree, Lovely and of Good Fruit.With
        the noise of a great tumultHe has kindled fire on it,And its branches are
        broken.
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Jeremiah\u2019s Life Threatened"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Life Threatened"
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor the Lord of hosts, who planted you, has pronounced doom
        against you for the evil of the house of Israel and of the house of Judah,
        which they have done against themselves to provoke Me to anger in offering
        incense to Baal.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the Lord gave me knowledge of  it, and I know it; for You showed
        me their doings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But I was like a docile lamb brought to the slaughter; and I did
        not know that they had devised schemes against me, saying, \u201CLet us destroy
        the tree with its fruit, and let us cut him off from the land of the living,
        that his name may be remembered no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: But, O Lord of hosts,You who judge righteously,Testing the mind and
        the heart,Let me see Your vengeance on them,For to You I have revealed my
        cause.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord concerning the men of Anathoth
        who seek your life, saying, \u2018Do not prophesy in the name of the Lord,
        lest you die by our hand\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord of hosts: \u2018Behold, I will punish
        them. The young men shall die by the sword, their sons and their daughters
        shall die by famine; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and there shall be no remnant of them, for I will bring catastrophe
        on the men of Anathoth, even  the year of their punishment.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Question"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Question"
      number: 1
      content: Righteous are You, O Lord, when I plead with You;Yet let me talk with
        You about Your judgments.Why does the way of the wicked prosper?Why are those
        happy who deal so treacherously?
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: You have planted them, yes, they have taken root;They grow, yes, they
        bear fruit.You are near in their mouthBut far from their mind.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But You, O Lord, know me;You have seen me,And You have tested my heart
        toward You.Pull them out like sheep for the slaughter,And prepare them for
        the day of slaughter.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Lord Answers Jeremiah'
      title: The Lord Answers Jeremiah
      number: 4
      content: "How long will the land mourn,And the herbs of every field wither?The
        beasts and birds are consumed,For the wickedness of those who dwell there,Because
        they said, \u201CHe will not see our final end.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf you have run with the footmen, and they have wearied you,Then
        how can you contend with horses?And if in the land of peace,In  which you
        trusted, they  wearied  you,Then how will you do in the floodplain of the
        Jordan?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For even your brothers, the house of your father,Even they have dealt
        treacherously with you;Yes, they have called a multitude after you.Do not
        believe them,Even though they speak smooth words to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI have forsaken My house, I have left My heritage;I have given
        the dearly beloved of My soul into the hand of her enemies."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: My heritage is to Me like a lion in the forest;It cries out against
        Me;Therefore I have hated it.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My heritage is to Me like a speckled vulture;The vultures all around
        are against her.Come, assemble all the beasts of the field,Bring them to
        devour!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CMany rulers have destroyed My vineyard,They have trodden My
        portion underfoot;They have made My pleasant portion a desolate wilderness."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They have made it desolate;Desolate, it mourns to Me;The whole land
        is made desolate,Because no one takes it to heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The plunderers have comeOn all the desolate heights in the wilderness,For
        the sword of the Lord shall devourFrom one end of the land to the other end
        of the land;No flesh shall have peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They have sown wheat but reaped thorns;They have put themselves to
        pain but do not profit.But be ashamed of your harvestBecause of the fierce
        anger of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CAgainst all My evil neighbors who touch
        the inheritance which I have caused My people Israel to inherit\u2014behold,
        I will pluck them out of their land and pluck out the house of Judah from
        among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then it shall be, after I have plucked them out, that I will return
        and have compassion on them and bring them back, everyone to his heritage
        and everyone to his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And it shall be, if they will learn carefully the ways of My people,
        to swear by My name, \u2018As the Lord lives,\u2019 as they taught My people
        to swear by Baal, then they shall be established in the midst of My people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if they do not obey, I will utterly pluck up and destroy that
        nation,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Symbol of the Linen Sash'
      title: Symbol of the Linen Sash
      number: 1
      content: "Thus the Lord said to me: \u201CGo and get yourself a linen sash,
        and put it around your waist, but do not put it in water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So I got a sash according to the word of the Lord, and put it around
        my waist.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to me the second time, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTake the sash that you acquired, which is around your waist,
        and arise, go to the Euphrates, and hide it there in a hole in the rock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So I went and hid it by the Euphrates, as the Lord commanded me.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now it came to pass after many days that the Lord said to me, \u201CArise,
        go to the Euphrates, and take from there the sash which I commanded you to
        hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then I went to the Euphrates and dug, and I took the sash from the
        place where I had hidden it; and there was the sash, ruined. It was profitable
        for nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018In this manner I will ruin the pride
        of Judah and the great pride of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This evil people, who refuse to hear My words, who follow the dictates
        of their hearts, and walk after other gods to serve them and worship them,
        shall be just like this sash which is profitable for nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Symbol of the Wine Bottles'
      title: Symbol of the Wine Bottles
      number: 11
      content: "For as the sash clings to the waist of a man, so I have caused the
        whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah to cling to Me,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018that they may become My people, for renown, for praise,
        and for glory; but they would not hear.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore you shall speak to them this word: \u2018Thus says
        the Lord God of Israel: \u201CEvery bottle shall be filled with wine.\u201D
        \u2019And they will say to you, \u2018Do we not certainly know that every
        bottle will be filled with wine?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold,
        I will fill all the inhabitants of this land\u2014even the kings who sit
        on David\u2019s throne, the priests, the prophets, and all the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem\u2014with drunkenness! "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Pride Precedes Captivity'
      title: Pride Precedes Captivity
      number: 14
      content: "And I will dash them one against another, even the fathers and the
        sons together,\u201D says the Lord. \u201CI will not pity nor spare nor have
        mercy, but will destroy them.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Hear and give ear:Do not be proud,For the Lord has spoken.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Give glory to the Lord your GodBefore He causes darkness,And before
        your feet stumbleOn the dark mountains,And while you are looking for light,He
        turns it into the shadow of deathAnd makes it dense darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not hear it,My soul will weep in secret for your
        pride;My eyes will weep bitterlyAnd run down with tears,Because the Lord\u2019s
        flock has been taken captive."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Say to the king and to the queen mother,\u201CHumble yourselves;Sit
        down,For your rule shall collapse, the crown of your glory.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The cities of the South shall be shut up,And no one shall open them;Judah
        shall be carried away captive, all of it;It shall be wholly carried away
        captive.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Lift up your eyes and seeThose who come from the north.Where is the
        flock that was given to you,Your beautiful sheep?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: What will you say when He punishes you?For you have taught themTo 
        be chieftains, to be head over you.Will not pangs seize you,Like a woman
        in labor?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And if you say in your heart,\u201CWhy have these things come upon
        me?\u201DFor the greatness of your iniquityYour skirts have been uncovered,Your
        heels made bare."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Can the Ethiopian change his skin or the leopard its spots?Then may
        you also do good who are accustomed to do evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will scatter them like stubbleThat passes away
        by the wind of the wilderness."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This is your lot,The portion of your measures from Me,\u201D says
        the Lord,\u201CBecause you have forgotten MeAnd trusted in falsehood."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Therefore I will uncover your skirts over your face,That your shame
        may appear.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "I have seen your adulteriesAnd your lustful  neighings,The lewdness
        of your harlotry,Your abominations on the hills in the fields.Woe to you,
        O Jerusalem!Will you still not be made clean?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sword, Famine, and Pestilence'
      title: Sword, Famine, and Pestilence
      number: 1
      content: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah concerning the droughts.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CJudah mourns,And her gates languish;They mourn for the land,And
        the cry of Jerusalem has gone up."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Their nobles have sent their lads for water;They went to the cisterns
        and found no water.They returned with their vessels empty;They were ashamed
        and confoundedAnd covered their heads.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Because the ground is parched,For there was no rain in the land,The
        plowmen were ashamed;They covered their heads.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Yes, the deer also gave birth in the field,But left because there
        was no grass.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the wild donkeys stood in the desolate heights;They sniffed at
        the wind like jackals;Their eyes failed because there  was no grass.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "O Lord, though our iniquities testify against us,Do it for Your name\u2019s
        sake;For our backslidings are many,We have sinned against You."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: O the Hope of Israel, his Savior in time of trouble,Why should You
        be like a stranger in the land,And like a traveler who turns aside to tarry
        for a night?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Why should You be like a man astonished,Like a mighty one who cannot
        save?Yet You, O Lord, are in our midst,And we are called by Your name;Do
        not leave us!
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Thus says the Lord to this people:\u201CThus they have loved to wander;They
        have not restrained their feet.Therefore the Lord does not accept them;He
        will remember their iniquity now,And punish their sins.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CDo not pray for this people, for
        their good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When they fast, I will not hear their cry; and when they offer burnt
        offering and grain offering, I will not accept them. But I will consume them
        by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord God! Behold, the prophets say to them,
        \u2018You shall not see the sword, nor shall you have famine, but I will
        give you assured peace in this place.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the Lord said to me, \u201CThe prophets prophesy lies in My name.
        I have not sent them, commanded them, nor spoken to them; they prophesy to
        you a false vision, divination, a worthless thing, and the deceit of their
        heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord concerning the prophets who prophesy
        in My name, whom I did not send, and who say, \u2018Sword and famine shall
        not be in this land\u2019\u2014\u2018By sword and famine those prophets shall
        be consumed! "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the people to whom they prophesy shall be cast out in the streets
        of Jerusalem because of the famine and the sword; they will have no one to
        bury them\u2014them nor their wives, their sons nor their daughters\u2014for
        I will pour their wickedness on them.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore you shall say this word to them:\u2018Let my eyes
        flow with tears night and day,And let them not cease;For the virgin daughter
        of my peopleHas been broken with a mighty stroke, with a very severe blow."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The People Plead for Mercy'
      title: The People Plead for Mercy
      number: 18
      content: "If I go out to the field,Then behold, those slain with the sword!And
        if I enter the city,Then behold, those sick from famine!Yes, both prophet
        and priest go about in a land they do not know.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Have You utterly rejected Judah?Has Your soul loathed Zion?Why have
        You stricken us so that there  is no healing for us?We looked for peace,
        but there  was no good;And for the time of healing, and there was trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: We acknowledge, O Lord, our wickednessAnd the iniquity of our fathers,For
        we have sinned against You.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Do not abhor us, for Your name\u2019s sake;Do not disgrace the throne
        of Your glory.Remember, do not break Your covenant with us."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Are there any among the idols of the nations that can cause rain?Or
        can the heavens give showers?Are You not He, O Lord our God?Therefore we
        will wait for You,Since You have made all these.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord Will Not Relent'
      title: The Lord Will Not Relent
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CEven if Moses and Samuel stood before
        Me, My mind would not be favorable toward this people. Cast them out of My
        sight, and let them go forth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it shall be, if they say to you, \u2018Where should we go?\u2019
        then you shall tell them, \u2018Thus says the Lord:\u201CSuch as are for
        death, to death;And such as are for the sword, to the sword;And such as are
        for the famine, to the famine;And such as are for the captivity, to the captivity.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd I will appoint over them four forms of  destruction,\u201D
        says the Lord: \u201Cthe sword to slay, the dogs to drag, the birds of the
        heavens and the beasts of the earth to devour and destroy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I will hand them over to trouble, to all kingdoms of the earth, because
        of Manasseh the son of Hezekiah, king of Judah, for what he did in Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor who will have pity on you, O Jerusalem?Or who will bemoan
        you?Or who will turn aside to ask how you are doing?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You have forsaken Me,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CYou have gone backward.Therefore
        I will stretch out My hand against you and destroy you;I am weary of relenting!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And I will winnow them with a winnowing fan in the gates of the land;I
        will bereave them of children;I will destroy My people,Since they do not
        return from their ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Their widows will be increased to Me more than the sand of the seas;I
        will bring against them,Against the mother of the young men,A plunderer at
        noonday;I will cause anguish and terror to fall on them suddenly.
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jeremiah\u2019s Dejection"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Dejection"
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CShe languishes who has borne seven;She has breathed her last;Her
        sun has gone downWhile it  was yet day;She has been ashamed and confounded.And
        the remnant of them I will deliver to the swordBefore their enemies,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Woe is me, my mother,That you have borne me,A man of strife and a
        man of contention to the whole earth!I have neither lent for interest,Nor
        have men lent to me for interest.Every one of them curses me.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord said:\u201CSurely it will be well with your remnant;Surely
        I will cause the enemy to intercede with youIn the time of adversity and
        in the time of affliction."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Can anyone break iron,The northern iron and the bronze?
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Your wealth and your treasuresI will give as plunder without price,Because
        of all your sins,Throughout your territories.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will make you cross over with your enemiesInto a land which
        you do not know;For a fire is kindled in My anger,Which shall burn upon you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: O Lord, You know;Remember me and visit me,And take vengeance for me
        on my persecutors.In Your enduring patience, do not take me away.Know that
        for Your sake I have suffered rebuke.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Your words were found, and I ate them,And Your word was to me the
        joy and rejoicing of my heart;For I am called by Your name,O Lord God of
        hosts.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I did not sit in the assembly of the mockers,Nor did I rejoice;I sat
        alone because of Your hand,For You have filled me with indignation.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Lord Reassures Jeremiah'
      title: The Lord Reassures Jeremiah
      number: 18
      content: Why is my pain perpetualAnd my wound incurable,Which refuses to be
        healed?Will You surely be to me like an unreliable stream,As waters that
        fail?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord:\u201CIf you return,Then I will bring
        you back;You shall stand before Me;If you take out the precious from the
        vile,You shall be as My mouth.Let them return to you,But you must not return
        to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And I will make you to this people a fortified bronze wall;And they
        will fight against you,But they shall not prevail against you;For I am with
        you to save youAnd deliver you,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI will deliver you from the hand of the wicked,And I will redeem
        you from the grip of the terrible.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Life-Style and Message"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Life-Style and Message"
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord also came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take a wife, nor shall you have sons or daughters
        in this place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For thus says the Lord concerning the sons and daughters who are
        born in this place, and concerning their mothers who bore them and their
        fathers who begot them in this land: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey shall die gruesome deaths; they shall not be lamented
        nor shall they be buried, but they shall be like refuse on the face of the
        earth. They shall be consumed by the sword and by famine, and their corpses
        shall be meat for the birds of heaven and for the beasts of the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For thus says the Lord: \u201CDo not enter the house of mourning,
        nor go to lament or bemoan them; for I have taken away My peace from this
        people,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Clovingkindness and mercies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Both the great and the small shall die in this land. They shall not
        be buried; neither shall men lament for them, cut themselves, nor make themselves
        bald for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nor shall men break bread in mourning for them, to comfort them for
        the dead; nor shall men give them the cup of consolation to drink for their
        father or their mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also you shall not go into the house of feasting to sit with them,
        to eat and drink.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CBehold,
        I will cause to cease from this place, before your eyes and in your days,
        the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom
        and the voice of the bride."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall be, when you show this people all these words,
        and they say to you, \u2018Why has the Lord pronounced all this great disaster
        against us? Or what is our iniquity? Or what is our sin that we have committed
        against the Lord our God?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "then you shall say to them, \u2018Because your fathers have forsaken
        Me,\u2019 says the Lord; \u2018they have walked after other gods and have
        served them and worshiped them, and have forsaken Me and not kept My law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you have done worse than your fathers, for behold, each one follows
        the dictates of his own evil heart, so that no one listens to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: God Will Restore Israel'
      title: God Will Restore Israel
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore I will cast you out of this land into a land that you do
        not know, neither you nor your fathers; and there you shall serve other gods
        day and night, where I will not show you favor.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cthat it shall no more be said, \u2018The Lord lives who brought up
        the children of Israel from the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but, \u2018The Lord lives who brought up the children of Israel from
        the land of the north and from all the lands where He had driven them.\u2019
        For I will bring them back into their land which I gave to their fathers."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBehold, I will send for many fishermen,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cand they shall fish them; and afterward I will send for many hunters,
        and they shall hunt them from every mountain and every hill, and out of the
        holes of the rocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For My eyes are on all their ways; they are not hidden from My face,
        nor is their iniquity hidden from My eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And first I will repay double for their iniquity and their sin, because
        they have defiled My land; they have filled My inheritance with the carcasses
        of their detestable and abominable idols.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "O Lord, my strength and my fortress,My refuge in the day of affliction,The
        Gentiles shall come to YouFrom the ends of the earth and say,\u201CSurely
        our fathers have inherited lies,Worthlessness and unprofitable things.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Will a man make gods for himself,Which are not gods?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, I will this once cause them to know,I will
        cause them to knowMy hand and My might;And they shall know that My name is
        the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Sin and Punishment"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Sin and Punishment"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CThe sin of Judah is  written with a pen of iron;With the point
        of a diamond it  is  engravedOn the tablet of their heart,And on the horns
        of your altars,"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: While their children rememberTheir altars and their wooden imagesBy
        the green trees on the high hills.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: O My mountain in the field,I will give as plunder your wealth, all
        your treasures,And your high places of sin within all your borders.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you, even yourself,Shall let go of your heritage which I gave
        you;And I will cause you to serve your enemiesIn the land which you do not
        know;For you have kindled a fire in My anger which shall burn forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CCursed is the man who trusts in manAnd makes
        flesh his strength,Whose heart departs from the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For he shall be like a shrub in the desert,And shall not see when
        good comes,But shall inhabit the parched places in the wilderness,In a salt
        land which  is not inhabited.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBlessed  is the man who trusts in the Lord,And whose hope is
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: For he shall be like a tree planted by the waters,Which spreads out
        its roots by the river,And will not fear when heat comes;But its leaf will
        be green,And will not be anxious in the year of drought,Nor will cease from
        yielding fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe heart is deceitful above all things,And desperately wicked;Who
        can know it?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I, the Lord, search the heart,I test the mind,Even to give every man
        according to his ways,According to the fruit of his doings.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAs a partridge that broods but does not hatch,So  is he who
        gets riches, but not by right;It will leave him in the midst of his days,And
        at his end he will be a fool.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: A glorious high throne from the beginningIs the place of our sanctuary.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jeremiah Prays for Deliverance'
      title: Jeremiah Prays for Deliverance
      number: 13
      content: "O Lord, the hope of Israel,All who forsake You shall be ashamed.\u201CThose
        who depart from MeShall be written in the earth,Because they have forsaken
        the Lord,The fountain of living waters.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Heal me, O Lord, and I shall be healed;Save me, and I shall be saved,For
        You are my praise.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Indeed they say to me,\u201CWhere is the word of the Lord?Let it
        come now!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: As for me, I have not hurried away from being a shepherd who follows
        You,Nor have I desired the woeful day;You know what came out of my lips;It
        was right there before You.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Do not be a terror to me;You are my hope in the day of doom.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Hallow the Sabbath Day'
      title: Hallow the Sabbath Day
      number: 18
      content: Let them be ashamed who persecute me,But do not let me be put to shame;Let
        them be dismayed,But do not let me be dismayed.Bring on them the day of doom,And
        destroy them with double destruction!
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Thus the Lord said to me: \u201CGo and stand in the gate of the children
        of the people, by which the kings of Judah come in and by which they go out,
        and in all the gates of Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, you kings of Judah,
        and all Judah, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, who enter by these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CTake heed to yourselves, and bear no burden
        on the Sabbath day, nor bring it in by the gates of Jerusalem; "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'nor carry a burden out of your houses on the Sabbath day, nor do
        any work, but hallow the Sabbath day, as I commanded your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But they did not obey nor incline their ear, but made their neck stiff,
        that they might not hear nor receive instruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall be, if you heed Me carefully,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cto bring no burden through the gates of this city on the Sabbath day,
        but hallow the Sabbath day, to do no work in it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then shall enter the gates of this city kings and princes sitting
        on the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, they and their
        princes, accompanied by the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem;
        and this city shall remain forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And they shall come from the cities of Judah and from the places around
        Jerusalem, from the land of Benjamin and from the lowland, from the mountains
        and from the South, bringing burnt offerings and sacrifices, grain offerings
        and incense, bringing sacrifices of praise to the house of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut if you will not heed Me to hallow the Sabbath day, such
        as not carrying a burden when entering the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath
        day, then I will kindle a fire in its gates, and it shall devour the palaces
        of Jerusalem, and it shall not be quenched.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Potter and the Clay'
      title: The Potter and the Clay
      number: 1
      content: 'The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CArise and go down to the potter\u2019s house, and there I will
        cause you to hear My words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then I went down to the potter\u2019s house, and there he was, making
        something at the wheel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And the vessel that he made of clay was marred in the hand of the
        potter; so he made it again into another vessel, as it seemed good to the
        potter to make.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to me, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO house of Israel, can I not do with you as this potter?\u201D
        says the Lord. \u201CLook, as the clay is in the potter\u2019s hand, so are
        you in My hand, O house of Israel! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The instant I speak concerning a nation and concerning a kingdom,
        to pluck up, to pull down, and to destroy it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'if that nation against whom I have spoken turns from its evil, I
        will relent of the disaster that I thought to bring upon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the instant I speak concerning a nation and concerning a kingdom,
        to build and to plant it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: if it does evil in My sight so that it does not obey My voice, then
        I will relent concerning the good with which I said I would benefit it.
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Warning Rejected"
      title: "God\u2019s Warning Rejected"
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, speak to the men of Judah and to the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, I am fashioning
        a disaster and devising a plan against you. Return now every one from his
        evil way, and make your ways and your doings good.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they said, \u201CThat is hopeless! So we will walk according
        to our own plans, and we will every one obey the dictates of his evil heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord:\u201CAsk now among the Gentiles,Who
        has heard such things?The virgin of Israel has done a very horrible thing."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Will a  man leave the snow water of Lebanon,Which  comes from the
        rock of the field?Will the cold flowing waters be forsaken for strange waters?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBecause My people have forgotten Me,They have burned incense
        to worthless idols.And they have caused themselves to stumble in their ways,From
        the ancient paths,To walk in pathways and not on a highway,"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: To make their land desolate and a perpetual hissing;Everyone who passes
        by it will be astonishedAnd shake his head.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jeremiah Persecuted'
      title: Jeremiah Persecuted
      number: 17
      content: "I will scatter them as with an east wind before the enemy;I will
        show them the back and not the faceIn the day of their calamity.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they said, \u201CCome and let us devise plans against Jeremiah;
        for the law shall not perish from the priest, nor counsel from the wise,
        nor the word from the prophet. Come and let us attack him with the tongue,
        and let us not give heed to any of his words.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Give heed to me, O Lord,And listen to the voice of those who contend
        with me!
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Shall evil be repaid for good?For they have dug a pit for my life.Remember
        that I stood before YouTo speak good for them,To turn away Your wrath from
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Therefore deliver up their children to the famine,And pour out their
        bloodBy the force of the sword;Let their wives become widowsAnd bereaved
        of their children.Let their men be put to death,Their young men be slainBy
        the sword in battle.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Let a cry be heard from their houses,When You bring a troop suddenly
        upon them;For they have dug a pit to take me,And hidden snares for my feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet, Lord, You know all their counselWhich is against me, to slay
        me.Provide no atonement for their iniquity,Nor blot out their sin from Your
        sight;But let them be overthrown before You.Deal thus with themIn the time
        of Your anger.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sign of the Broken Flask'
      title: The Sign of the Broken Flask
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CGo and get a potter\u2019s earthen flask,
        and take some of the elders of the people and some of the elders of the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And go out to the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, which is by the entry
        of the Potsherd Gate; and proclaim there the words that I will tell you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and say, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, O kings of Judah and inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CBehold,
        I will bring such a catastrophe on this place, that whoever hears of it,
        his ears will tingle."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBecause they have forsaken Me and made this an alien place,
        because they have burned incense in it to other gods whom neither they, their
        fathers, nor the kings of Judah have known, and have filled this place with
        the blood of the innocents "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '(they have also built the high places of Baal, to burn their sons
        with fire for burnt offerings to Baal, which I did not command or speak,
        nor did it come into My mind), '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "therefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat
        this place shall no more be called Tophet or the Valley of the Son of Hinnom,
        but the Valley of Slaughter. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will make void the counsel of Judah and Jerusalem in this place,
        and I will cause them to fall by the sword before their enemies and by the
        hands of those who seek their lives; their corpses I will give as meat for
        the birds of the heaven and for the beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will make this city desolate and a hissing; everyone who passes
        by it will be astonished and hiss because of all its plagues. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will cause them to eat the flesh of their sons and the flesh
        of their daughters, and everyone shall eat the flesh of his friend in the
        siege and in the desperation with which their enemies and those who seek
        their lives shall drive them to despair.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen you shall break the flask in the sight of the men who
        go with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts: \u201CEven so
        I will break this people and this city, as one breaks a potter\u2019s vessel,
        which cannot be made whole again; and they shall bury them in Tophet till
        there  is no place to bury. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Thus I will do to this place,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cand to its
        inhabitants, and make this city like Tophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah
        shall be defiled like the place of Tophet, because of all the houses on whose
        roofs they have burned incense to all the host of heaven, and poured out
        drink offerings to other gods.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jeremiah came from Tophet, where the Lord had sent him to prophesy;
        and he stood in the court of the Lord\u2019s house and said to all the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Behold,
        I will bring on this city and on all her towns all the doom that I have pronounced
        against it, because they have stiffened their necks that they might not hear
        My words.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Word of God to Pashhur'
      title: The Word of God to Pashhur
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Pashhur the son of Immer, the priest who was also chief governor
        in the house of the Lord, heard that Jeremiah prophesied these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Then Pashhur struck Jeremiah the prophet, and put him in the stocks
        that were in the high gate of Benjamin, which was by the house of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And it happened on the next day that Pashhur brought Jeremiah out
        of the stocks. Then Jeremiah said to him, \u201CThe Lord has not called your
        name Pashhur, but Magor-Missabib. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will make you a terror to
        yourself and to all your friends; and they shall fall by the sword of their
        enemies, and your eyes shall see it. I will give all Judah into the hand
        of the king of Babylon, and he shall carry them captive to Babylon and slay
        them with the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover I will deliver all the wealth of this city, all its produce,
        and all its precious things; all the treasures of the kings of Judah I will
        give into the hand of their enemies, who will plunder them, seize them, and
        carry them to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Jeremiah\u2019s Unpopular Ministry"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Unpopular Ministry"
      number: 6
      content: "And you, Pashhur, and all who dwell in your house, shall go into
        captivity. You shall go to Babylon, and there you shall die, and be buried
        there, you and all your friends, to whom you have prophesied lies.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: O Lord, You induced me, and I was persuaded;You are stronger than
        I, and have prevailed.I am in derision daily;Everyone mocks me.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For when I spoke, I cried out;I shouted, \u201CViolence and plunder!\u201DBecause
        the word of the Lord was made to meA reproach and a derision daily."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I said, \u201CI will not make mention of Him,Nor speak anymore
        in His name.\u201DBut His  word was in my heart like a burning fireShut up
        in my bones;I was weary of holding it back,And I could not."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For I heard many mocking:\u201CFear on every side!\u201D\u201CReport,\u201D
        they  say, \u201Cand we will report it!\u201DAll my acquaintances watched
        for my stumbling, saying,\u201CPerhaps he can be induced;Then we will prevail
        against him,And we will take our revenge on him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But the Lord  is  with me as a mighty, awesome One.Therefore my persecutors
        will stumble, and will not prevail.They will be greatly ashamed, for they
        will not prosper.Their  everlasting confusion will never be forgotten.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But, O Lord of hosts,You who test the righteous,And see the mind and
        heart,Let me see Your vengeance on them;For I have pleaded my cause before
        You.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Sing to the Lord! Praise the Lord!For He has delivered the life of
        the poorFrom the hand of evildoers.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Cursed be the day in which I was born!Let the day not be blessed in
        which my mother bore me!
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Let the man be cursedWho brought news to my father, saying,\u201CA
        male child has been born to you!\u201DMaking him very glad."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And let that man be like the citiesWhich the Lord  overthrew, and
        did not relent;Let him hear the cry in the morningAnd the shouting at noon,
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Because he did not kill me from the womb,That my mother might have
        been my grave,And her womb always enlarged with  me.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Why did I come forth from the womb to see labor and sorrow,That my
        days should be consumed with shame?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jerusalem\u2019s Doom Is Sealed"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Doom Is Sealed"
      number: 1
      content: 'The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord when King Zedekiah
        sent to him Pashhur the son of Melchiah, and Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah,
        the priest, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlease inquire of the Lord for us, for Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon makes war against us. Perhaps the Lord will deal with us according
        to all His wonderful works, that the  king may go away from us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them, \u201CThus you shall say to Zedekiah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel: \u201CBehold, I will turn
        back the weapons of war that are in your hands, with which you fight against
        the king of Babylon and the Chaldeans who besiege you outside the walls;
        and I will assemble them in the midst of this city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I Myself will fight against you with an outstretched hand and with
        a strong arm, even in anger and fury and great wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will strike the inhabitants of this city, both man and beast; they
        shall die of a great pestilence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And afterward,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will deliver Zedekiah
        king of Judah, his servants and the people, and such as are left in this
        city from the pestilence and the sword and the famine, into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, into the hand of their enemies, and into the hand of those
        who seek their life; and he shall strike them with the edge of the sword.
        He shall not spare them, or have pity or mercy.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CNow you shall say to this people, \u2018Thus says the Lord:
        \u201CBehold, I set before you the way of life and the way of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who remains in this city shall die by the sword, by famine, and
        by pestilence; but he who goes out and defects to the Chaldeans who besiege
        you, he shall live, and his life shall be as a prize to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Message to the House of David'
      title: Message to the House of David
      number: 10
      content: "For I have set My face against this city for adversity and not for
        good,\u201D says the Lord. \u201CIt shall be given into the hand of the king
        of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd concerning the house of the king of Judah, say, \u2018Hear
        the word of the Lord, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O house of David! Thus says the Lord:\u201CExecute judgment in the
        morning;And deliver him  who  is plunderedOut of the hand of the oppressor,Lest
        My fury go forth like fireAnd burn so that no one can quench it,Because of
        the evil of your doings."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you, O inhabitant of the valley,And rock
        of the plain,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CWho say, \u2018Who shall come down
        against us?Or who shall enter our dwellings?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But I will punish you according to the fruit of your doings,\u201D
        says the Lord;\u201CI will kindle a fire in its forest,And it shall devour
        all things around it.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CGo down to the house of the king of Judah,
        and there speak this word, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and say, \u2018Hear the word of the Lord, O king of Judah, you who
        sit on the throne of David, you and your servants and your people who enter
        these gates! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u201CExecute judgment and righteousness, and
        deliver the plundered out of the hand of the oppressor. Do no wrong and do
        no violence to the stranger, the fatherless, or the widow, nor shed innocent
        blood in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For if you indeed do this thing, then shall enter the gates of this
        house, riding on horses and in chariots, accompanied by servants and people,
        kings who sit on the throne of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if you will not hear these words, I swear by Myself,\u201D says
        the Lord, \u201Cthat this house shall become a desolation.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says the Lord to the house of the king of Judah:\u201CYou
        are  Gilead to Me,The head of Lebanon;Yet I surely will make you a wilderness,Cities
        which are not inhabited."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: I will prepare destroyers against you,Everyone with his weapons;They
        shall cut down your choice cedarsAnd cast them into the fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And many nations will pass by this city; and everyone will say to
        his neighbor, \u2018Why has the Lord done so to this great city?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they will answer, \u2018Because they have forsaken the covenant
        of the Lord their God, and worshiped other gods and served them.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Message to the Sons of Josiah'
      title: Message to the Sons of Josiah
      number: 10
      content: Weep not for the dead, nor bemoan him;Weep bitterly for him who goes
        away,For he shall return no more,Nor see his native country.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus says the Lord concerning Shallum the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah, who reigned instead of Josiah his father, who went from this place:
        \u201CHe shall not return here anymore, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: but he shall die in the place where they have led him captive, and
        shall see this land no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWoe to him who builds his house by unrighteousnessAnd his chambers
        by injustice,Who uses his neighbor\u2019s service without wagesAnd gives
        him nothing for his work,"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Who says, \u2018I will build myself a wide house with spacious chambers,And
        cut out windows for it,Paneling it with cedarAnd painting it with vermilion.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CShall you reign because you enclose yourself in cedar?Did not
        your father eat and drink,And do justice and righteousness?Then it  was well
        with him."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He judged the cause of the poor and needy;Then it  was well.Was not
        this knowing Me?\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYet your eyes and your heart are for nothing but your covetousness,For
        shedding innocent blood,And practicing oppression and violence.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah:\u201CThey shall not lament for him,Saying,  \u2018Alas, my
        brother!\u2019 or \u2018Alas, my sister!\u2019They shall not lament for him,Saying,
        \u2018Alas, master!\u2019 or \u2018Alas, his glory!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He shall be buried with the burial of a donkey,Dragged and cast out
        beyond the gates of Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGo up to Lebanon, and cry out,And lift up your voice in Bashan;Cry
        from Abarim,For all your lovers are destroyed."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I spoke to you in your prosperity,But you said, \u2018I will not
        hear.\u2019This has  been your manner from your youth,That you did not obey
        My voice."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The wind shall eat up all your rulers,And your lovers shall go into
        captivity;Surely then you will be ashamed and humiliatedFor all your wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Message to Coniah'
      title: Message to Coniah
      number: 23
      content: O inhabitant of Lebanon,Making your nest in the cedars,How gracious
        will you be when pangs come upon you,Like the pain of a woman in labor?
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthough Coniah the son
        of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, were the signet on My right hand, yet I would
        pluck you off; "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and I will give you into the hand of those who seek your life, and
        into the hand of  those whose face you fear\u2014the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and the hand of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So I will cast you out, and your mother who bore you, into another
        country where you were not born; and there you shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: But to the land to which they desire to return, there they shall not
        return.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIs this man Coniah a despised, broken idol\u2014A vessel in
        which is no pleasure?Why are they cast out, he and his descendants,And cast
        into a land which they do not know?"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: O earth, earth, earth,Hear the word of the Lord!
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u2018Write this man down as childless,A man who
        shall not prosper in his days;For none of his descendants shall prosper,Sitting
        on the throne of David,And ruling anymore in Judah.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Branch of Righteousness'
      title: The Branch of Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWoe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the sheep of My
        pasture!\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord God of Israel against the shepherds
        who feed My people: \u201CYou have scattered My flock, driven them away,
        and not attended to them. Behold, I will attend to you for the evil of your
        doings,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBut I will gather the remnant of My flock out of all countries
        where I have driven them, and bring them back to their folds; and they shall
        be fruitful and increase. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will set up shepherds over them who will feed them; and they shall
        fear no more, nor be dismayed, nor shall they be lacking,\u201D says the
        Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat
        I will raise to David a Branch of righteousness;A King shall reign and prosper,And
        execute judgment and righteousness in the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In His days Judah will be saved,And Israel will dwell safely;Now this
        is His name by which He will be called:THE LORD OUR RIGHTEOUSNESS.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,
        \u201Cthat they shall no longer say, \u2018As the Lord lives who brought
        up the children of Israel from the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: False Prophets and Empty Oracles'
      title: False Prophets and Empty Oracles
      number: 8
      content: "but, \u2018As the Lord lives who brought up and led the descendants
        of the house of Israel from the north country and from all the countries
        where I had driven them.\u2019 And they shall dwell in their own land.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: My heart within me is brokenBecause of the prophets;All my bones shake.I
        am like a drunken man,And like a man whom wine has overcome,Because of the
        Lord,And because of His holy words.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For the land is full of adulterers;For because of a curse the land
        mourns.The pleasant places of the wilderness are dried up.Their course of
        life is evil,And their might is not right.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFor both prophet and priest are profane;Yes, in My house I
        have found their wickedness,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore their way shall be to themLike slippery ways;In the
        darkness they shall be driven onAnd fall in them;For I will bring disaster
        on them,The year of their punishment,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd I have seen folly in the prophets of Samaria:They prophesied
        by BaalAnd caused My people Israel to err."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Also I have seen a horrible thing in the prophets of Jerusalem:They
        commit adultery and walk in lies;They also strengthen the hands of evildoers,So
        that no one turns back from his wickedness.All of them are like Sodom to
        Me,And her inhabitants like Gomorrah.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord of hosts concerning the prophets:\u2018Behold,
        I will feed them with wormwood,And make them drink the water of gall;For
        from the prophets of JerusalemProfaneness has gone out into all the land.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CDo not listen to the words of the
        prophets who prophesy to you.They make you worthless;They speak a vision
        of their own heart,Not from the mouth of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They continually say to those who despise Me,\u2018The Lord has said,
        \u201CYou shall have peace\u201D \u2019;And to everyone who walks according
        to the dictates of his own heart, they say,\u2018No evil shall come upon
        you.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For who has stood in the counsel of the Lord,And has perceived and
        heard His word?Who has marked His word and heard it?
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Behold, a whirlwind of the Lord has gone forth in fury\u2014A violent
        whirlwind!It will fall violently on the head of the wicked."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The anger of the Lord will not turn backUntil He has executed and
        performed the thoughts of His heart.In the latter days you will understand
        it perfectly.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI have not sent these prophets, yet they ran.I have not spoken
        to them, yet they prophesied."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But if they had stood in My counsel,And had caused My people to hear
        My words,Then they would have turned them from their evil wayAnd from the
        evil of their doings.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAm I a God near at hand,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd not
        a God afar off?"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Can anyone hide himself in secret places,So I shall not see him?\u201D
        says the Lord;\u201CDo I not fill heaven and earth?\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have heard what the prophets have said who prophesy lies
        in My name, saying, \u2018I have dreamed, I have dreamed!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'How long will this be in the heart of the prophets who prophesy lies?
        Indeed they  are prophets of the deceit of their own heart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: who try to make My people forget My name by their dreams which everyone
        tells his neighbor, as their fathers forgot My name for Baal.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThe prophet who has a dream, let him tell a dream;And he who
        has My word, let him speak My word faithfully.What is the chaff to the wheat?\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIs not My word like a fire?\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd like
        a hammer that breaks the rock in pieces?"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, I am against the prophets,\u201D says the
        Lord, \u201Cwho steal My words every one from his neighbor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, I am  against the prophets,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cwho
        use their tongues and say, \u2018He says.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Behold, I am against those who prophesy false dreams,\u201D says
        the Lord, \u201Cand tell them, and cause My people to err by their lies and
        by their recklessness. Yet I did not send them or command them; therefore
        they shall not profit this people at all,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CSo when these people or the prophet or the priest ask you,
        saying, \u2018What is the oracle of the Lord?\u2019 you shall then say to
        them, \u2018What oracle?\u2019 I will even forsake you,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CAnd as  for the prophet and the priest and the people who say,
        \u2018The oracle of the Lord!\u2019 I will even punish that man and his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus every one of you shall say to his neighbor, and every one to
        his brother, \u2018What has the Lord answered?\u2019 and, \u2018What has
        the Lord spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And the oracle of the Lord you shall mention no more. For every man\u2019s
        word will be his oracle, for you have perverted the words of the living God,
        the Lord of hosts, our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus you shall say to the prophet, \u2018What has the Lord answered
        you?\u2019 and, \u2018What has the Lord spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But since you say, \u2018The oracle of the Lord!\u2019 therefore
        thus says the Lord: \u2018Because you say this word, \u201CThe oracle of
        the Lord!\u201D and I have sent to you, saying, \u201CDo not say, \u2018The
        oracle of the Lord!\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'therefore behold, I, even I, will utterly forget you and forsake
        you, and the city that I gave you and your fathers, and will  cast  you out
        of My presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And I will bring an everlasting reproach upon you, and a perpetual
        shame, which shall not be forgotten.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sign of Two Baskets of Figs'
      title: The Sign of Two Baskets of Figs
      number: 1
      content: 'The Lord showed me, and there were two baskets of figs set before
        the temple of the Lord, after Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had carried
        away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, and the princes
        of Judah with the craftsmen and smiths, from Jerusalem, and had brought them
        to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'One basket had very good figs, like the figs that  are first ripe;
        and the other basket had very bad figs which could not be eaten, they were
        so bad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CWhat do you see, Jeremiah?\u201DAnd
        I said, \u201CFigs, the good figs, very good; and the bad, very bad, which
        cannot be eaten, they are so bad.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018Like these good
        figs, so will I acknowledge those who are carried away captive from Judah,
        whom I have sent out of this place for their  own good, into the land of
        the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I will set My eyes on them for good, and I will bring them back
        to this land; I will build them and not pull them down, and I will plant
        them and not pluck them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then I will give them a heart to know Me, that I am the Lord; and
        they shall be My people, and I will be their God, for they shall return to
        Me with their whole heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018And as the bad figs which cannot be eaten, they are so bad\u2019\u2014surely
        thus says the Lord\u2014\u2018so will I give up Zedekiah the king of Judah,
        his princes, the residue of Jerusalem who remain in this land, and those
        who dwell in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will deliver them to trouble into all the kingdoms of the earth,
        for their harm, to  be a reproach and a byword, a taunt and a curse, in all
        places where I shall drive them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I will send the sword, the famine, and the pestilence among them,
        till they are consumed from the land that I gave to them and their fathers.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seventy Years of Desolation'
      title: Seventy Years of Desolation
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah,
        in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah (which was
        the first year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah and to
        all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFrom the thirteenth year of Josiah the son of Amon, king of
        Judah, even to this day, this is the twenty-third year in which the word
        of the Lord has come to me; and I have spoken to you, rising early and speaking,
        but you have not listened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the Lord has sent to you all His servants the prophets, rising
        early and sending them, but you have not listened nor inclined your ear to
        hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They said, \u2018Repent now everyone of his evil way and his evil
        doings, and dwell in the land that the Lord has given to you and your fathers
        forever and ever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Do not go after other gods to serve them and worship them, and do
        not provoke Me to anger with the works of your hands; and I will not harm
        you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet you have not listened to Me,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat
        you might provoke Me to anger with the works of your hands to your own hurt."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord of hosts: \u2018Because you have
        not heard My words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "behold, I will send and take all the families of the north,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018and Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, My servant,
        and will bring them against this land, against its inhabitants, and against
        these nations all around, and will utterly destroy them, and make them an
        astonishment, a hissing, and perpetual desolations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover I will take from them the voice of mirth and the voice of
        gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the sound
        of the millstones and the light of the lamp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And this whole land shall be a desolation and an astonishment, and
        these nations shall serve the king of Babylon seventy years.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018Then it will come to pass, when seventy years are completed,
        that I will punish the king of Babylon and that nation, the land of the Chaldeans,
        for their iniquity,\u2019 says the Lord; \u2018and I will make it a perpetual
        desolation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So I will bring on that land all My words which I have pronounced
        against it, all that is written in this book, which Jeremiah has prophesied
        concerning all the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Judgment on the Nations'
      title: Judgment on the Nations
      number: 14
      content: "(For many nations and great kings shall be served by them also; and
        I will repay them according to their deeds and according to the works of
        their own hands.)\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the Lord God of Israel to me: \u201CTake this wine
        cup of fury from My hand, and cause all the nations, to whom I send you,
        to drink it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they will drink and stagger and go mad because of the sword that
        I will send among them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I took the cup from the Lord\u2019s hand, and made all the nations
        drink, to whom the Lord had sent me: "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jerusalem and the cities of Judah, its kings and its princes, to
        make them a desolation, an astonishment, a hissing, and a curse, as it  is
        this day; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pharaoh king of Egypt, his servants, his princes, and all his people; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'all the mixed multitude, all the kings of the land of Uz, all the
        kings of the land of the Philistines (namely, Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron, and
        the remnant of Ashdod); '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Edom, Moab, and the people of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'all the kings of Tyre, all the kings of Sidon, and the kings of the
        coastlands which are across the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Dedan, Tema, Buz, and all who  are in the farthest corners; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'all the kings of Arabia and all the kings of the mixed multitude
        who dwell in the desert; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'all the kings of Zimri, all the kings of Elam, and all the kings
        of the Medes; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: all the kings of the north, far and near, one with another; and all
        the kingdoms of the world which are on the face of the earth. Also the king
        of Sheshach shall drink after them.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CTherefore you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of
        hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CDrink, be drunk, and vomit! Fall and rise
        no more, because of the sword which I will send among you.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And it shall be, if they refuse to take the cup from your hand to
        drink, then you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts: \u201CYou
        shall certainly drink! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For behold, I begin to bring calamity on the city which is called
        by My name, and should you be utterly unpunished? You shall not be unpunished,
        for I will call for a sword on all the inhabitants of the earth,\u201D says
        the Lord of hosts.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore prophesy against them all these words, and say to
        them:\u2018The Lord will roar from on high,And utter His voice from His holy
        habitation;He will roar mightily against His fold.He will give a shout, as
        those who tread the  grapes,Against all the inhabitants of the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "A noise will come to the ends of the earth\u2014For the Lord has
        a controversy with the nations;He will plead His case with all flesh.He will
        give those who  are wicked to the sword,\u2019 says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CBehold, disaster shall go forthFrom
        nation to nation,And a great whirlwind shall be raised upFrom the farthest
        parts of the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And at that day the slain of the Lord shall be from one end of the
        earth even to the other end of the earth. They shall not be lamented, or
        gathered, or buried; they shall become refuse on the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CWail, shepherds, and cry!Roll about in  the  ashes,You leaders
        of the flock!For the days of your slaughter and your dispersions are fulfilled;You
        shall fall like a precious vessel."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And the shepherds will have no way to flee,Nor the leaders of the
        flock to escape.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: A voice of the cry of the shepherds,And a wailing of the leaders to
        the flock will  be  heard.For the Lord has plundered their pasture,
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: And the peaceful dwellings are cut downBecause of the fierce anger
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He has left His lair like the lion;For their land is desolateBecause
        of the fierceness of the Oppressor,And because of His fierce anger.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Saved from Death'
      title: Jeremiah Saved from Death
      number: 1
      content: 'In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah, this word came from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Stand in the court of the Lord\u2019s
        house, and speak to all the cities of Judah, which come to worship in the
        Lord\u2019s house, all the words that I command you to speak to them. Do
        not diminish a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Perhaps everyone will listen and turn from his evil way, that I may
        relent concerning the calamity which I purpose to bring on them because of
        the evil of their doings.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CIf you
        will not listen to Me, to walk in My law which I have set before you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'to heed the words of My servants the prophets whom I sent to you,
        both rising up early and sending them (but you have not heeded), '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then I will make this house like Shiloh, and will make this city
        a curse to all the nations of the earth.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah
        speaking these words in the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now it happened, when Jeremiah had made an end of speaking all that
        the Lord had commanded him to speak to all the people, that the priests and
        the prophets and all the people seized him, saying, \u201CYou will surely
        die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why have you prophesied in the name of the Lord, saying, \u2018This
        house shall be like Shiloh, and this city shall be desolate, without an inhabitant\u2019?\u201D
        And all the people were gathered against Jeremiah in the house of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the princes of Judah heard these things, they came up from the
        king\u2019s house to the house of the Lord and sat down in the entry of the
        New Gate of the Lord\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the priests and the prophets spoke to the princes and all the
        people, saying, \u201CThis man deserves to die! For he has prophesied against
        this city, as you have heard with your ears.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to all the princes and all the people, saying:
        \u201CThe Lord sent me to prophesy against this house and against this city
        with all the words that you have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now therefore, amend your ways and your doings, and obey the voice
        of the Lord your God; then the Lord will relent concerning the doom that
        He has pronounced against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As for me, here I am, in your hand; do with me as seems good and
        proper to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But know for certain that if you put me to death, you will surely
        bring innocent blood on yourselves, on this city, and on its inhabitants;
        for truly the Lord has sent me to you to speak all these words in your hearing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the princes and all the people said to the priests and the prophets,
        \u201CThis man does not deserve to die. For he has spoken to us in the name
        of the Lord our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then certain of the elders of the land rose up and spoke to all the
        assembly of the people, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CMicah of Moresheth prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king
        of Judah, and spoke to all the people of Judah, saying, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord of hosts:\u201CZion shall be plowed like a field,Jerusalem shall become
        heaps of ruins,And the mountain of the templeLike the bare hills of the forest.\u201D
        \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah ever put him to death? Did
        he not fear the Lord and seek the Lord\u2019s favor? And the Lord  relented
        concerning the doom which He had pronounced against them. But we are doing
        great evil against ourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now there was also a man who prophesied in the name of the Lord,
        Urijah the son of Shemaiah of Kirjath Jearim, who prophesied against this
        city and against this land according to all the words of Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty men and all the
        princes, heard his words, the king sought to put him to death; but when Urijah
        heard it, he was afraid and fled, and went to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Jehoiakim the king sent men to Egypt: Elnathan the son of Achbor,
        and other men who  went with him to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And they brought Urijah from Egypt and brought him to Jehoiakim the
        king, who killed him with the sword and cast his dead body into the graves
        of the common people.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Nevertheless the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah,
        so that they should not give him into the hand of the people to put him to
        death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Symbol of the Bonds and Yokes'
      title: Symbol of the Bonds and Yokes
      number: 1
      content: 'In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord to me: \u2018Make for yourselves bonds and
        yokes, and put them on your neck, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and send them to the king of Edom, the king of Moab, the king of
        the Ammonites, the king of Tyre, and the king of Sidon, by the hand of the
        messengers who come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And command them to say to their masters, \u201CThus says the Lord
        of hosts, the God of Israel\u2014thus you shall say to your masters: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018I have made the earth, the man and the beast that are on the
        ground, by My great power and by My outstretched arm, and have given it to
        whom it seemed proper to Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon, My servant; and the beasts of the field I have also
        given him to serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So all nations shall serve him and his son and his son\u2019s son,
        until the time of his land comes; and then many nations and great kings shall
        make him serve them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it shall be, that the nation and kingdom which will not serve
        Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, and which will not put its neck under
        the yoke of the king of Babylon, that nation I will punish,\u2019 says the
        Lord, \u2018with the sword, the famine, and the pestilence, until I have
        consumed them by his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore do not listen to your prophets, your diviners, your dreamers,
        your soothsayers, or your sorcerers, who speak to you, saying, \u201CYou
        shall not serve the king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they prophesy a lie to you, to remove you far from your land;
        and I will drive you out, and you will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the nations that bring their necks under the yoke of the king
        of Babylon and serve him, I will let them remain in their own land,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018and they shall till it and dwell in it.\u2019 \u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I also spoke to Zedekiah king of Judah according to all these words,
        saying, \u201CBring your necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and
        serve him and his people, and live! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Why will you die, you and your people, by the sword, by the famine,
        and by the pestilence, as the Lord has spoken against the nation that will
        not serve the king of Babylon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore do not listen to the words of the prophets who speak to
        you, saying, \u2018You shall not serve the king of Babylon,\u2019 for they
        prophesy a lie to you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "for I have not sent them,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cyet they prophesy
        a lie in My name, that I may drive you out, and that you may perish, you
        and the prophets who prophesy to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Also I spoke to the priests and to all this people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018Do not listen to the words of your prophets who prophesy
        to you, saying, \u201CBehold, the vessels of the Lord\u2019s house will now
        shortly be brought back from Babylon\u201D; for they prophesy a lie to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not listen to them; serve the king of Babylon, and live! Why should
        this city be laid waste? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if they are prophets, and if the word of the Lord is with them,
        let them now make intercession to the Lord of hosts, that the vessels which
        are left in the house of the Lord, in the house of the king of Judah, and
        at Jerusalem, do not go to Babylon.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord of hosts concerning the pillars, concerning
        the Sea, concerning the carts, and concerning the remainder of the vessels
        that remain in this city, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon did not take, when he carried
        away captive Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, from Jerusalem
        to Babylon, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'yes, thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning the
        vessels that remain in the house of the Lord, and in the house of the king
        of Judah and of Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018They shall be carried to Babylon, and there they shall be until
        the day that I visit them,\u2019 says the Lord. \u2018Then I will bring them
        up and restore them to this place.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hananiah\u2019s Falsehood and Doom"
      title: "Hananiah\u2019s Falsehood and Doom"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened in the same year, at the beginning of the reign of
        Zedekiah king of Judah, in the fourth year and in the fifth month, that Hananiah
        the son of Azur the prophet, who was from Gibeon, spoke to me in the house
        of the Lord in the presence of the priests and of all the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus speaks the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, saying: \u2018I
        have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Within two full years I will bring back to this place all the vessels
        of the Lord\u2019s house, that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took away from
        this place and carried to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I will bring back to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim,
        king of Judah, with all the captives of Judah who went to Babylon,\u2019
        says the Lord, \u2018for I will break the yoke of the king of Babylon.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the prophet Jeremiah spoke to the prophet Hananiah in the presence
        of the priests and in the presence of all the people who stood in the house
        of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and the prophet Jeremiah said, \u201CAmen! The Lord do so; the Lord
        perform your words which you have prophesied, to bring back the vessels of
        the Lord\u2019s house and all who were carried away captive, from Babylon
        to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nevertheless hear now this word that I speak in your hearing and
        in the hearing of all the people: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The prophets who have been before me and before you of old prophesied
        against many countries and great kingdoms\u2014of war and disaster and pestilence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "As for the prophet who prophesies of peace, when the word of the
        prophet comes to pass, the prophet will be known as one whom the Lord has
        truly sent.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Hananiah the prophet took the yoke off the prophet Jeremiah\u2019s
        neck and broke it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Hananiah spoke in the presence of all the people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018Even so I will break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon from the neck of all nations within the space of two full years.\u2019
        \u201D And the prophet Jeremiah went his way."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, after Hananiah the prophet
        had broken the yoke from the neck of the prophet Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo and tell Hananiah, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CYou
        have broken the yokes of wood, but you have made in their place yokes of
        iron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CI have
        put a yoke of iron on the neck of all these nations, that they may serve
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon; and they shall serve him. I have given him
        the beasts of the field also.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the prophet Jeremiah said to Hananiah the prophet, \u201CHear
        now, Hananiah, the Lord has not sent you, but you make this people trust
        in a lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will cast you from
        the face of the earth. This year you shall die, because you have taught rebellion
        against the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: So Hananiah the prophet died the same year in the seventh month.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Captives"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Captives"
      number: 1
      content: "Now these are the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent
        from Jerusalem to the remainder of the elders who were carried away captive\u2014to
        the priests, the prophets, and all the people whom Nebuchadnezzar had carried
        away captive from Jerusalem to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(This happened after Jeconiah the king, the queen mother, the eunuchs,
        the princes of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen, and the smiths had departed
        from Jerusalem.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The  letter  was  sent by the hand of Elasah the son of Shaphan, and
        Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to Babylon,
        to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, to all who were carried
        away captive, whom I have caused to be carried away from Jerusalem to Babylon:'
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Build houses and dwell in  them; plant gardens and eat their fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Take wives and beget sons and daughters; and take wives for your
        sons and give your daughters to husbands, so that they may bear sons and
        daughters\u2014that you may be increased there, and not diminished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And seek the peace of the city where I have caused you to be carried
        away captive, and pray to the Lord for it; for in its peace you will have
        peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: Do not let your
        prophets and your diviners who are in your midst deceive you, nor listen
        to your dreams which you cause to be dreamed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For they prophesy falsely to you in My name; I have not sent them,
        says the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For thus says the Lord: After seventy years are completed at Babylon,
        I will visit you and perform My good word toward you, and cause you to return
        to this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, says the Lord, thoughts
        of peace and not of evil, to give you a future and a hope. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then you will call upon Me and go and pray to Me, and I will listen
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you will seek Me and find Me, when you search for Me with all
        your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: I will be found by you, says the Lord, and I will bring you back from
        your captivity; I will gather you from all the nations and from all the places
        where I have driven you, says the Lord, and I will bring you to the place
        from which I cause you to be carried away captive.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u201CThe Lord has raised up prophets for
        us in Babylon\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord concerning the king who sits on the
        throne of David, concerning all the people who dwell in this city, and concerning
        your brethren who have not gone out with you into captivity\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'thus says the Lord of hosts: Behold, I will send on them the sword,
        the famine, and the pestilence, and will make them like rotten figs that
        cannot be eaten, they are so bad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will pursue them with the sword, with famine, and with pestilence;
        and I will deliver them to trouble among all the kingdoms of the earth\u2014to
        be a curse, an astonishment, a hissing, and a reproach among all the nations
        where I have driven them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because they have not heeded My words, says the Lord, which I sent
        to them by My servants the prophets, rising up early and sending them; neither
        would you heed, says the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Therefore hear the word of the Lord, all you of the captivity, whom
        I have sent from Jerusalem to Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, concerning Ahab the
        son of Kolaiah, and Zedekiah the son of Maaseiah, who prophesy a lie to you
        in My name: Behold, I will deliver them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon, and he shall slay them before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And because of them a curse shall be taken up by all the captivity
        of Judah who are in Babylon, saying, \u201CThe Lord make you like Zedekiah
        and Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire\u201D; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "because they have done disgraceful things in Israel, have committed
        adultery with their neighbors\u2019 wives, and have spoken lying words in
        My name, which I have not commanded them. Indeed I know, and am a witness,
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall also speak to Shemaiah the Nehelamite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Thus speaks the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, saying: You have
        sent letters in your name to all the people who are at Jerusalem, to Zephaniah
        the son of Maaseiah the priest, and to all the priests, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has made you priest instead of Jehoiada the priest,
        so that there should be officers in the house of the Lord over every man
        who is demented and considers himself a prophet, that you should put him
        in prison and in the stocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now therefore, why have you not rebuked Jeremiah of Anathoth who
        makes himself a prophet to you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For he has sent to us in Babylon, saying, \u2018This captivity  is
        long; build houses and dwell in  them, and plant gardens and eat their fruit.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the hearing of Jeremiah
        the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Send to all those in captivity, saying, Thus says the Lord concerning
        Shemaiah the Nehelamite: Because Shemaiah has prophesied to you, and I have
        not sent him, and he has caused you to trust in a lie\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'therefore thus says the Lord: Behold, I will punish Shemaiah the
        Nehelamite and his family: he shall not have anyone to dwell among this people,
        nor shall he see the good that I will do for My people, says the Lord, because
        he has taught rebellion against the Lord.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restoration of Israel and Judah'
      title: Restoration of Israel and Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus speaks the Lord God of Israel, saying: \u2018Write in
        a book for yourself all the words that I have spoken to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For behold, the days are coming,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018that
        I will bring back from captivity My people Israel and Judah,\u2019 says the
        Lord. \u2018And I will cause them to return to the land that I gave to their
        fathers, and they shall possess it.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now these are the words that the Lord spoke concerning Israel and
        Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord:\u2018We have heard a voice of trembling,Of
        fear, and not of peace."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Ask now, and see,Whether a man is ever in labor with child?So why
        do I see every man with his hands on his loinsLike a woman in labor,And all
        faces turned pale?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Alas! For that day is great,So that none is like it;And it is the
        time of Jacob\u2019s trouble,But he shall be saved out of it."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u2018For it shall come to pass in that day,\u2019Says the Lord of
        hosts,\u2018That I will break his yoke from your neck,And will burst your
        bonds;Foreigners shall no more enslave them."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: But they shall serve the Lord their God,And David their king,Whom
        I will raise up for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Therefore do not fear, O My servant Jacob,\u2019 says the Lord,\u2018Nor
        be dismayed, O Israel;For behold, I will save you from afar,And your seed
        from the land of their captivity.Jacob shall return, have rest and be quiet,And
        no one shall make him afraid."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I am with you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018to save you;Though
        I make a full end of all nations where I have scattered you,Yet I will not
        make a complete end of you.But I will correct you in justice,And will not
        let you go altogether unpunished.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord:\u2018Your affliction is incurable,Your
        wound is severe."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: There  is no one to plead your cause,That you may be bound up;You
        have no healing medicines.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: All your lovers have forgotten you;They do not seek you;For I have
        wounded you with the wound of an enemy,With the chastisement of a cruel one,For
        the multitude of your iniquities,Because your sins have increased.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Why do you cry about your affliction?Your sorrow is incurable.Because
        of the multitude of your iniquities,Because your sins have increased,I have
        done these things to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Therefore all those who devour you shall be devoured;And all
        your adversaries, every one of them, shall go into captivity;Those who plunder
        you shall become plunder,And all who prey upon you I will make a prey."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For I will restore health to youAnd heal you of your wounds,\u2019
        says the Lord,\u2018Because they called you an outcast saying:\u201CThis
        is Zion;No one seeks her.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord:\u2018Behold, I will bring back the captivity
        of Jacob\u2019s tents,And have mercy on his dwelling places;The city shall
        be built upon its own mound,And the palace shall remain according to its
        own plan."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then out of them shall proceed thanksgivingAnd the voice of those
        who make merry;I will multiply them, and they shall not diminish;I will also
        glorify them, and they shall not be small.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Their children also shall be as before,And their congregation shall
        be established before Me;And I will punish all who oppress them.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Their nobles shall be from among them,And their governor shall come
        from their midst;Then I will cause him to draw near,And he shall approach
        Me;For who is this who pledged his heart to approach Me?\u2019 says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018You shall be My people,And I will be your God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Behold, the whirlwind of the LordGoes forth with fury,A continuing
        whirlwind;It will fall violently on the head of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The fierce anger of the Lord will not return until He has done it,And
        until He has performed the intents of His heart.In the latter days you will
        consider it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Remnant of Israel Saved'
      title: The Remnant of Israel Saved
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CAt the same time,\u201D says the Lord, \u201CI will be the
        God of all the families of Israel, and they shall be My people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CThe people who survived the swordFound grace
        in the wilderness\u2014Israel, when I went to give him rest.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord has appeared of old to me, saying:\u201CYes, I have loved
        you with an everlasting love;Therefore with lovingkindness I have drawn you."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Again I will build you, and you shall be rebuilt,O virgin of Israel!You
        shall again be adorned with your tambourines,And shall go forth in the dances
        of those who rejoice.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: You shall yet plant vines on the mountains of Samaria;The planters
        shall plant and eat them as ordinary food.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For there shall be a dayWhen the watchmen will cry on Mount Ephraim,\u2018Arise,
        and let us go up to Zion,To the Lord our God.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CSing with gladness for Jacob,And shout
        among the chief of the nations;Proclaim, give praise, and say,\u2018O Lord,
        save Your people,The remnant of Israel!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Behold, I will bring them from the north country,And gather them from
        the ends of the earth,Among them the blind and the lame,The woman with childAnd
        the one who labors with child, together;A great throng shall return there.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They shall come with weeping,And with supplications I will lead them.I
        will cause them to walk by the rivers of waters,In a straight way in which
        they shall not stumble;For I am a Father to Israel,And Ephraim is My firstborn.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHear the word of the Lord, O nations,And declare it in the
        isles afar off, and say,\u2018He who scattered Israel will gather him,And
        keep him as a shepherd does his flock.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For the Lord has redeemed Jacob,And ransomed him from the hand of
        one stronger than he.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore they shall come and sing in the height of Zion,Streaming
        to the goodness of the Lord\u2014For wheat and new wine and oil,For the young
        of the flock and the herd;Their souls shall be like a well-watered garden,And
        they shall sorrow no more at all."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen shall the virgin rejoice in the dance,And the young men
        and the old, together;For I will turn their mourning to joy,Will comfort
        them,And make them rejoice rather than sorrow."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Mercy on Ephraim'
      title: Mercy on Ephraim
      number: 14
      content: "I will satiate the soul of the priests with abundance,And My people
        shall be satisfied with My goodness, says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CA voice was heard in Ramah,Lamentation and
        bitter weeping,Rachel weeping for her children,Refusing to be comforted for
        her children,Because they are no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CRefrain your voice from weeping,And your
        eyes from tears;For your work shall be rewarded, says the Lord,And they shall
        come back from the land of the enemy."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: There is hope in your future, says the Lord,That your children shall
        come back to their own border.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CI have surely heard Ephraim bemoaning himself:\u2018You have
        chastised me, and I was chastised,Like an untrained bull;Restore me, and
        I will return,For You are the Lord my God."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Surely, after my turning, I repented;And after I was instructed,
        I struck myself on the thigh;I was ashamed, yes, even humiliated,Because
        I bore the reproach of my youth.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Is Ephraim My dear son?Is  he a pleasant child?For though I spoke
        against him,I earnestly remember him still;Therefore My heart yearns for
        him;I will surely have mercy on him, says the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CSet up signposts,Make landmarks;Set your heart toward the highway,The
        way in which you went.Turn back, O virgin of Israel,Turn back to these your
        cities."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Future Prosperity of Judah'
      title: Future Prosperity of Judah
      number: 22
      content: "How long will you gad about,O you backsliding daughter?For the Lord
        has created a new thing in the earth\u2014A woman shall encompass a man.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CThey shall
        again use this speech in the land of Judah and in its cities, when I bring
        back their captivity: \u2018The Lord bless you, O home of justice, and  mountain
        of holiness!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And there shall dwell in Judah itself, and in all its cities together,
        farmers and those going out with flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I have satiated the weary soul, and I have replenished every
        sorrowful soul.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: After this I awoke and looked around, and my sleep was sweet to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming, says the Lord, that I will sow
        the house of Israel and the house of Judah with the seed of man and the seed
        of beast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, that as I have watched over them to pluck
        up, to break down, to throw down, to destroy, and to afflict, so I will watch
        over them to build and to plant, says the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "In those days they shall say no more:\u2018The fathers have eaten
        sour grapes,And the children\u2019s teeth are set on edge.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: A New Covenant'
      title: A New Covenant
      number: 30
      content: But every one shall die for his own iniquity; every man who eats the
        sour grapes, his teeth shall be set on edge.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming, says the Lord, when I will make
        a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers in the
        day that  I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt,
        My covenant which they broke, though I was a husband to them, says the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel
        after those days, says the Lord: I will put My law in their minds, and write
        it on their hearts; and I will be their God, and they shall be My people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "No more shall every man teach his neighbor, and every man his brother,
        saying, \u2018Know the Lord,\u2019 for they all shall know Me, from the least
        of them to the greatest of them, says the Lord. For I will forgive their
        iniquity, and their sin I will remember no more.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Thus says the Lord,Who gives the sun for a light by day,The ordinances
        of the moon and the stars for a light by night,Who disturbs the sea,And its
        waves roar(The Lord of hosts is His name):'
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CIf those ordinances departFrom before Me, says the Lord,Then
        the seed of Israel shall also ceaseFrom being a nation before Me forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CIf heaven above can be measured,And the
        foundations of the earth searched out beneath,I will also cast off all the
        seed of IsraelFor all that they have done, says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming, says the Lord, that the city shall
        be built for the Lord  from the Tower of Hananel to the Corner Gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The surveyor\u2019s line shall again extend straight forward over
        the hill Gareb; then it shall turn toward Goath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And the whole valley of the dead bodies and of the ashes, and all
        the fields as far as the Brook Kidron, to the corner of the Horse Gate toward
        the east, shall  be holy to the Lord. It shall not be plucked up or thrown
        down anymore forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Buys a Field'
      title: Jeremiah Buys a Field
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord  in the tenth year of
        Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For then the king of Babylon\u2019s army besieged Jerusalem, and
        Jeremiah the prophet was shut up in the court of the prison, which was  in
        the king of Judah\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Zedekiah king of Judah had shut him up, saying, \u201CWhy do
        you prophesy and say, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, I will give
        this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Zedekiah king of Judah shall not escape from the hand of the
        Chaldeans, but shall surely be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon,
        and shall speak with him face to face, and see him eye to eye; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "then he shall lead Zedekiah to Babylon, and there he shall be until
        I visit him,\u201D says the Lord; \u201Cthough you fight with the Chaldeans,
        you shall not succeed\u201D \u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Jeremiah said, \u201CThe word of the Lord came to me, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018Behold, Hanamel the son of Shallum your uncle will come to
        you, saying, \u201CBuy my field which is in Anathoth, for the right of redemption
        is yours to buy it.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hanamel my uncle\u2019s son came to me in the court of the prison
        according to the word of the Lord, and said to me, \u2018Please buy my field
        that is in Anathoth, which is in the country of Benjamin; for the right of
        inheritance is yours, and the redemption yours; buy it for yourself.\u2019
        Then I knew that this was the word of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I bought the field from Hanamel, the son of my uncle who was in
        Anathoth, and weighed out  to him the money\u2014seventeen shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And I signed the deed and sealed it, took witnesses, and weighed
        the money on the scales. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So I took the purchase deed, both that which was sealed according
        to the law and custom, and that which was open; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and I gave the purchase deed to Baruch the son of Neriah, son of
        Mahseiah, in the presence of Hanamel my uncle\u2019s son, and in the presence
        of the witnesses who signed the purchase deed, before all the Jews who sat
        in the court of the prison."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen I charged Baruch before them, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CTake
        these deeds, both this purchase deed which is sealed and this deed which
        is open, and put them in an earthen vessel, that they may last many days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jeremiah Prays for Understanding'
      title: Jeremiah Prays for Understanding
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CHouses
        and fields and vineyards shall be possessed again in this land.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow when I had delivered the purchase deed to Baruch the son
        of Neriah, I prayed to the Lord, saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Ah, Lord God! Behold, You have made the heavens and the earth
        by Your great power and outstretched arm. There is nothing too hard for You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "You show lovingkindness to thousands, and repay the iniquity of the
        fathers into the bosom of their children after them\u2014the Great, the Mighty
        God, whose name is  the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You  are  great in counsel and mighty in work, for Your eyes are
        open to all the ways of the sons of men, to give everyone according to his
        ways and according to the fruit of his doings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You have set signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, to this day,
        and in Israel and among other men; and You have made Yourself a name, as
        it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have brought Your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with
        signs and wonders, with a strong hand and an outstretched arm, and with great
        terror; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You have given them this land, of which You swore to their fathers
        to give them\u2014\u201Ca land flowing with milk and honey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And they came in and took possession of it, but they have not obeyed
        Your voice or walked in Your law. They have done nothing of all that You
        commanded them to do; therefore You have caused all this calamity to come
        upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Look, the siege mounds! They have come to the city to take
        it; and the city has been given into the hand of the Chaldeans who fight
        against it, because of the sword and famine and pestilence. What You have
        spoken has happened; there You see it!  "
      comments: []
    - name: "25: God\u2019s Assurance of the People\u2019s Return"
      title: "God\u2019s Assurance of the People\u2019s Return"
      number: 25
      content: "And You have said to me, O Lord God, \u201CBuy the field for money,
        and take witnesses\u201D!\u2014yet the city has been given into the hand
        of the Chaldeans.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am the Lord, the God of all flesh. Is there anything
        too hard for Me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will give this city
        into the hand of the Chaldeans, into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon,
        and he shall take it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the Chaldeans who fight against this city shall come and set
        fire to this city and burn it, with the houses on whose roofs they have offered
        incense to Baal and poured out drink offerings to other gods, to provoke
        Me to anger; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "because the children of Israel and the children of Judah have done
        only evil before Me from their youth. For the children of Israel have provoked
        Me only to anger with the work of their hands,\u2019 says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u2018For this city has been to Me a  provocation  of My anger and
        My fury from the day that they built it, even to this day; so I will remove
        it from before My face "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "because of all the evil of the children of Israel and the children
        of Judah, which they have done to provoke Me to anger\u2014they, their kings,
        their princes, their priests, their prophets, the men of Judah, and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they have turned to Me the back, and not the face; though I taught
        them, rising up early and teaching them, yet they have not listened to receive
        instruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But they set their abominations in the house which is called by My
        name, to defile it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And they built the high places of Baal which are in the Valley of
        the Son of Hinnom, to cause their sons and their daughters to pass through
        the  fire to Molech, which I did not command them, nor did it come into My
        mind that they should do this abomination, to cause Judah to sin.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, concerning
        this city of which you say, \u2018It shall be delivered into the hand of
        the king of Babylon by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence\u2019: "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Behold, I will gather them out of all countries where I have driven
        them in My anger, in My fury, and in great wrath; I will bring them back
        to this place, and I will cause them to dwell safely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They shall be My people, and I will be their God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then I will give them one heart and one way, that they may fear Me
        forever, for the good of them and their children after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And I will make an everlasting covenant with them, that I will not
        turn away from doing them good; but I will put My fear in their hearts so
        that they will not depart from Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Yes, I will rejoice over them to do them good, and I will assuredly
        plant them in this land, with all My heart and with all My soul.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord: \u2018Just as I have brought all this
        great calamity on this people, so I will bring on them all the good that
        I have promised them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And fields will be bought in this land of which you say, \u201CIt 
        is desolate, without man or beast; it has been given into the hand of the
        Chaldeans.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Men will buy fields for money, sign deeds and seal them, and take
        witnesses, in the land of Benjamin, in the places around Jerusalem, in the
        cities of Judah, in the cities of the mountains, in the cities of the lowland,
        and in the cities of the South; for I will cause their captives to return,\u2019
        says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Excellence of the Restored Nation'
      title: Excellence of the Restored Nation
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah a second time, while
        he was still shut up in the court of the prison, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord  who made it, the Lord who formed it to
        establish it (the Lord  is His name): "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Call to Me, and I will answer you, and show you great and mighty
        things, which you do not know.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord, the God of Israel, concerning the houses
        of this city and the houses of the kings of Judah, which have been pulled
        down to  fortify against the siege mounds and the sword: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018They come to fight with the Chaldeans, but only to fill their
        places with the dead bodies of men whom I will slay in My anger and My fury,
        all for whose wickedness I have hidden My face from this city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, I will bring it health and healing; I will heal them and
        reveal to them the abundance of peace and truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And I will cause the captives of Judah and the captives of Israel
        to return, and will rebuild those places as at the first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will cleanse them from all their iniquity by which they have sinned
        against Me, and I will pardon all their iniquities by which they have sinned
        and by which they have transgressed against Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then it shall be to Me a name of joy, a praise, and an honor before
        all nations of the earth, who shall hear all the good that I do to them;
        they shall fear and tremble for all the goodness and all the prosperity that
        I provide for it.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Again there shall be heard in this
        place\u2014of which you say, \u201CIt is desolate, without man and without
        beast\u201D\u2014in the cities of Judah, in the streets of Jerusalem that
        are desolate, without man and without inhabitant and without beast, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "the voice of joy and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom
        and the voice of the bride, the voice of those who will say:\u201CPraise
        the Lord of hosts,For the Lord  is good,For His mercy endures forever\u201D\u2014and
        of those who  will bring the sacrifice of praise into the house of the Lord.
        For I will cause the captives of the land to return as at the first,\u2019
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts: \u2018In this place which is desolate,
        without man and without beast, and in all its cities, there shall again be
        a dwelling place of shepherds causing their flocks to lie down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "In the cities of the mountains, in the cities of the lowland, in
        the cities of the South, in the land of Benjamin, in the places around Jerusalem,
        and in the cities of Judah, the flocks shall again pass under the hands of
        him who counts them,\u2019 says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Behold, the days are coming,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018that
        I will perform that good thing which I have promised to the house of Israel
        and to the house of Judah:"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u2018In those days and at that timeI will cause to grow up to DavidA
        Branch of righteousness;He shall execute judgment and righteousness in the
        earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In those days Judah will be saved,And Jerusalem will dwell safely.And
        this is  the  name by which she will be called:THE LORD OUR RIGHTEOUSNESS.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord: \u2018David shall never lack a man
        to sit on the throne of the house of Israel; "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: The Permanence of God\u2019s Covenant"
      title: "The Permanence of God\u2019s Covenant"
      number: 18
      content: "nor shall the priests, the Levites, lack a man to offer burnt offerings
        before Me, to kindle grain offerings, and to sacrifice continually.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018If you can break My covenant with
        the day and My covenant with the night, so that there will not be day and
        night in their season, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'then My covenant may also be broken with David My servant, so that
        he shall not have a son to reign on his throne, and with the Levites, the
        priests, My ministers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As the host of heaven cannot be numbered, nor the sand of the sea
        measured, so will I multiply the descendants of David My servant and the
        Levites who minister to Me.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Moreover the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHave you not considered what these people have spoken, saying,
        \u2018The two families which the Lord has chosen, He has also cast them off\u2019?
        Thus they have despised My people, as if they should no more be a nation
        before them."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018If My covenant is not with day and
        night, and  if I have not appointed the ordinances of heaven and earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then I will cast away the descendants of Jacob and David My servant,
        so that I will not take any of his descendants to  be rulers over the descendants
        of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. For I will cause their captives to return,
        and will have mercy on them.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zedekiah Warned by God'
      title: Zedekiah Warned by God
      number: 1
      content: 'The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord, when Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and all his army, all the kingdoms of the earth under his
        dominion, and all the people, fought against Jerusalem and all its cities,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018Go and speak to
        Zedekiah king of Judah and tell him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Behold,
        I will give this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall
        burn it with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And you shall not escape from his hand, but shall surely be taken
        and delivered into his hand; your eyes shall see the eyes of the king of
        Babylon, he shall speak with you face to face, and you shall go to Babylon.\u2019
        \u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet hear the word of the Lord, O Zedekiah king of Judah! Thus says
        the Lord concerning you: \u2018You shall not die by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You shall die in peace; as in the ceremonies of your fathers, the
        former kings who were before you, so they shall burn incense for you and
        lament for you, saying, \u201CAlas, lord!\u201D For I have pronounced the
        word, says the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke all these words to Zedekiah king
        of Judah in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Treacherous Treatment of Slaves'
      title: Treacherous Treatment of Slaves
      number: 7
      content: "when the king of Babylon\u2019s army fought against Jerusalem and
        all the cities of Judah that were left, against Lachish and Azekah; for only 
        these fortified cities remained of the cities of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This  is the word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord, after King
        Zedekiah had made a covenant with all the people who were at Jerusalem to
        proclaim liberty to them: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "that every man should set free his male and female slave\u2014a Hebrew
        man or woman\u2014that no one should keep a Jewish brother in bondage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now when all the princes and all the people, who had entered into
        the covenant, heard that everyone should set free his male and female slaves,
        that no one should keep them in bondage anymore, they obeyed and let them
        go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: But afterward they changed their minds and made the male and female
        slaves return, whom they had set free, and brought them into subjection as
        male and female slaves.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018I made a covenant
        with your fathers in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt,
        out of the house of bondage, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAt the end of seven years let every man set free his Hebrew
        brother, who has been sold to him; and when he has served you six years,
        you shall let him go free from you.\u201D But your fathers did not obey Me
        nor incline their ear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then you recently turned and did what was right in My sight\u2014every
        man proclaiming liberty to his neighbor; and you made a covenant before Me
        in the house which is called by My name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then you turned around and profaned My name, and every one of you
        brought back his male and female slaves, whom you had set at liberty, at
        their pleasure, and brought them back into subjection, to be your male and
        female slaves.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord: \u2018You have not obeyed Me
        in proclaiming liberty, every one to his brother and every one to his neighbor.
        Behold, I proclaim liberty to you,\u2019 says the Lord\u2014\u2018to the
        sword, to pestilence, and to famine! And I will deliver you to trouble among
        all the kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will give the men who have transgressed My covenant, who have
        not performed the words of the covenant which they made before Me, when they
        cut the calf in two and passed between the parts of it\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "the princes of Judah, the princes of Jerusalem, the eunuchs, the
        priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the parts of the
        calf\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will give them into the hand of their enemies and into the hand
        of those who seek their life. Their dead bodies shall be for meat for the
        birds of the heaven and the beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I will give Zedekiah king of Judah and his princes into the hand
        of their enemies, into the hand of those who seek their life, and into the
        hand of the king of Babylon\u2019s army which has gone back from you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Behold, I will command,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and cause them
        to return to this city. They will fight against it and take it and burn it
        with fire; and I will make the cities of Judah a desolation without inhabitant.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Obedient Rechabites'
      title: The Obedient Rechabites
      number: 1
      content: 'The word which came to Jeremiah from the Lord in the days of Jehoiakim
        the son of Josiah, king of Judah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the house of the Rechabites, speak to them, and bring
        them into the house of the Lord, into one of the chambers, and give them
        wine to drink.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I took Jaazaniah the son of Jeremiah, the son of Habazziniah,
        his brothers and all his sons, and the whole house of the Rechabites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and I brought them into the house of the Lord, into the chamber of
        the sons of Hanan the son of Igdaliah, a man of God, which was by the chamber
        of the princes, above the chamber of Maaseiah the son of Shallum, the keeper
        of the door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I set before the sons of the house of the Rechabites bowls full
        of wine, and cups; and I said to them, \u201CDrink wine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But they said, \u201CWe will drink no wine, for Jonadab the son of
        Rechab, our father, commanded us, saying, \u2018You shall drink no wine,
        you nor your sons, forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You shall not build a house, sow seed, plant a vineyard, nor have
        any  of  these; but all your days you shall dwell in tents, that you may
        live many days in the land where you are sojourners.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Thus we have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father,
        in all that he charged us, to drink no wine all our days, we, our wives,
        our sons, or our daughters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'nor to build ourselves houses to dwell in; nor do we have vineyard,
        field, or seed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But we have dwelt in tents, and have obeyed and done according to
        all that Jonadab our father commanded us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But it came to pass, when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up
        into the land, that we said, \u2018Come, let us go to Jerusalem for fear
        of the army of the Chaldeans and for fear of the army of the Syrians.\u2019
        So we dwell at Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then came the word of the Lord to Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Go and
        tell the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, \u201CWill you not
        receive instruction to obey My words?\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe words of Jonadab the son of Rechab, which he commanded
        his sons, not to drink wine, are performed; for to this day they drink none,
        and obey their father\u2019s commandment. But although I have spoken to you,
        rising early and speaking, you did not obey Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I have also sent to you all My servants the prophets, rising up early
        and sending them, saying, \u2018Turn now everyone from his evil way, amend
        your doings, and do not go after other gods to serve them; then you will
        dwell in the land which I have given you and your fathers.\u2019 But you
        have not inclined your ear, nor obeyed Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Surely the sons of Jonadab the son of Rechab have performed the commandment
        of their father, which he commanded them, but this people has not obeyed
        Me.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord God of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u2018Behold, I will bring on Judah and on all the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        all the doom that I have pronounced against them; because I have spoken to
        them but they have not heard, and I have called to them but they have not
        answered.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Jeremiah said to the house of the Rechabites, \u201CThus says
        the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Because you have obeyed the commandment
        of Jonadab your father, and kept all his precepts and done according to all
        that he commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CJonadab
        the son of Rechab shall not lack a man to stand before Me forever.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Scroll Read in the Temple'
      title: The Scroll Read in the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah, that this word came to Jeremiah from the Lord, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake a scroll of a book and write on it all the words that
        I have spoken to you against Israel, against Judah, and against all the nations,
        from the day I spoke to you, from the days of Josiah even to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the adversities which
        I purpose to bring upon them, that everyone may turn from his evil way, that
        I may forgive their iniquity and their sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeremiah called Baruch the son of Neriah; and Baruch wrote on
        a scroll of a book, at the instruction of Jeremiah, all the words of the
        Lord which He had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Jeremiah commanded Baruch, saying, \u201CI am confined, I cannot
        go into the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You go, therefore, and read from the scroll which you have written
        at my instruction, the words of the Lord, in the hearing of the people in
        the Lord\u2019s house on the day of fasting. And you shall also read them
        in the hearing of all Judah who come from their cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It may be that they will present their supplication before the Lord,
        and everyone will turn from his evil way. For great is the anger and the
        fury that the Lord has pronounced against this people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Baruch the son of Neriah did according to all that Jeremiah the
        prophet commanded him, reading from the book the words of the Lord in the
        Lord\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah, in the ninth month, that they proclaimed a fast before the
        Lord to all the people in Jerusalem, and to all the people who came from
        the cities of Judah to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Scroll Read in the Palace'
      title: The Scroll Read in the Palace
      number: 10
      content: "Then Baruch read from the book the words of Jeremiah in the house
        of the Lord, in the chamber of Gemariah the son of Shaphan the scribe, in
        the upper court at the entry of the New Gate of the Lord\u2019s house, in
        the hearing of all the people."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Michaiah the son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, heard all
        the words of the Lord from the book, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "he then went down to the king\u2019s house, into the scribe\u2019s
        chamber; and there all the princes were sitting\u2014Elishama the scribe,
        Delaiah the son of Shemaiah, Elnathan the son of Achbor, Gemariah the son
        of Shaphan, Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and all the princes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Michaiah declared to them all the words that he had heard when
        Baruch read the book in the hearing of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore all the princes sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, the son
        of Shelemiah, the son of Cushi, to Baruch, saying, \u201CTake in your hand
        the scroll from which you have read in the hearing of the people, and come.\u201D
        So Baruch the son of Neriah took the scroll in his hand and came to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CSit down now, and read it in our hearing.\u201D
        So Baruch read it in their hearing."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now it happened, when they had heard all the words, that they looked
        in fear from one to another, and said to Baruch, \u201CWe will surely tell
        the king of all these words.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they asked Baruch, saying, \u201CTell us now, how did you write
        all these words\u2014at his instruction?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Baruch answered them, \u201CHe proclaimed with his mouth all these
        words to me, and I wrote them with ink in the book.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "19: The King Destroys Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll"
      title: "The King Destroys Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll"
      number: 19
      content: "Then the princes said to Baruch, \u201CGo and hide, you and Jeremiah;
        and let no one know where you are.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they went to the king, into the court; but they stored the scroll
        in the chamber of Elishama the scribe, and told all the words in the hearing
        of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So the king sent Jehudi to bring the scroll, and he took it from
        Elishama the scribe\u2019s chamber. And Jehudi read it in the hearing of
        the king and in the hearing of all the princes who stood beside the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the king was sitting in the winter house in the ninth month,
        with a  fire burning on the hearth before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it happened, when Jehudi had read three or four columns, that 
        the  king cut it with the scribe\u2019s knife and cast it into the fire that
        was on the hearth, until all the scroll was consumed in the fire that was
        on the hearth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yet they were not afraid, nor did they tear their garments, the king
        nor any of his servants who heard all these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Nevertheless Elnathan, Delaiah, and Gemariah implored the king not
        to burn the scroll; but he would not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll'
      title: Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll
      number: 26
      content: "And the king commanded Jerahmeel the king\u2019s son, Seraiah the
        son of Azriel, and Shelemiah the son of Abdeel, to seize Baruch the scribe
        and Jeremiah the prophet, but the Lord hid them."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now after the king had burned the scroll with the words which Baruch
        had written at the instruction of Jeremiah, the word of the Lord came to
        Jeremiah, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTake yet another scroll, and write on it all the former words
        that were in the first scroll which Jehoiakim the king of Judah has burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And you shall say to Jehoiakim king of Judah, \u2018Thus says the
        Lord: \u201CYou have burned this scroll, saying, \u2018Why have you written
        in it that the king of Babylon will certainly come and destroy this land,
        and cause man and beast to cease from here?\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah:
        \u201CHe shall have no one to sit on the throne of David, and his dead body
        shall be cast out to the heat of the day and the frost of the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I will punish him, his family, and his servants for their iniquity;
        and I will bring on them, on the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and on the men
        of Judah all the doom that I have pronounced against them; but they did not
        heed.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to Baruch the scribe,
        the son of Neriah, who wrote on it at the instruction of Jeremiah all the
        words of the book which Jehoiakim king of Judah had burned in the fire. And
        besides, there were added to them many similar words.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zedekiah\u2019s Vain Hope"
      title: "Zedekiah\u2019s Vain Hope"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now King Zedekiah the son of Josiah reigned instead of Coniah the
        son of Jehoiakim, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon made king in the land
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: But neither he nor his servants nor the people of the land gave heed
        to the words of the Lord which He spoke by the prophet Jeremiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Zedekiah the king sent Jehucal the son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah
        the son of Maaseiah, the priest, to the prophet Jeremiah, saying, \u201CPray
        now to the Lord our God for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Jeremiah was coming and going among the people, for they had
        not yet put him in prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Pharaoh\u2019s army came up from Egypt; and when the Chaldeans
        who were besieging Jerusalem heard news of them, they departed from Jerusalem."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to the prophet Jeremiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018Thus you shall
        say to the king of Judah, who sent you to Me to inquire of Me: \u201CBehold,
        Pharaoh\u2019s army which has come up to help you will return to Egypt, to
        their own land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Chaldeans shall come back and fight against this city, and
        take it and burn it with fire.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u2018Do not deceive yourselves, saying, \u201CThe
        Chaldeans will surely depart from us,\u201D for they will not depart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Imprisoned'
      title: Jeremiah Imprisoned
      number: 10
      content: "For though you had defeated the whole army of the Chaldeans who fight
        against you, and there remained only wounded men among them, they would rise
        up, every man in his tent, and burn the city with fire.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And it happened, when the army of the Chaldeans left the  siege of
        Jerusalem for fear of Pharaoh\u2019s army, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'that Jeremiah went out of Jerusalem to go into the land of Benjamin
        to claim his property there among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when he was in the Gate of Benjamin, a captain of the guard was
        there whose name was Irijah the son of Shelemiah, the son of Hananiah; and
        he seized Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CYou are defecting to the Chaldeans!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jeremiah said, \u201CFalse! I am not defecting to the Chaldeans.\u201D
        But he did not listen to him.So Irijah seized Jeremiah and brought him to
        the princes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Therefore the princes were angry with Jeremiah, and they struck him
        and put him in prison in the house of Jonathan the scribe. For they had made
        that the prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Jeremiah entered the dungeon and the cells, and Jeremiah had
        remained there many days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "then Zedekiah the king sent and took him out. The king asked him
        secretly in his house, and said, \u201CIs there any word from the Lord?\u201DAnd
        Jeremiah said, \u201CThere is.\u201D Then he said, \u201CYou shall be delivered
        into the hand of the king of Babylon!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Moreover Jeremiah said to King Zedekiah, \u201CWhat offense have
        I committed against you, against your servants, or against this people, that
        you have put me in prison? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Where now are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not come against you or against this land\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore please hear now, O my lord the king. Please, let my petition
        be accepted before you, and do not make me return to the house of Jonathan
        the scribe, lest I die there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Zedekiah the king commanded that they should commit Jeremiah
        to the court of the prison, and that they should give him daily a piece of
        bread from the bakers\u2019 street, until all the bread in the city was gone.
        Thus Jeremiah remained in the court of the prison."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah in the Dungeon'
      title: Jeremiah in the Dungeon
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Shephatiah the son of Mattan, Gedaliah the son of Pashhur, Jucal
        the son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur the son of Malchiah heard the words that
        Jeremiah had spoken to all the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018He who remains in this city shall
        die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence; but he who goes over to the
        Chaldeans shall live; his life shall be as a prize to him, and he shall live.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord: \u2018This city shall surely be given into the
        hand of the king of Babylon\u2019s army, which shall take it.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore the princes said to the king, \u201CPlease, let this man
        be put to death, for thus he weakens the hands of the men of war who remain
        in this city, and the hands of all the people, by speaking such words to
        them. For this man does not seek the welfare of this people, but their harm.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Zedekiah the king said, \u201CLook, he is in your hand. For
        the king can do nothing against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they took Jeremiah and cast him into the dungeon of Malchiah the
        king\u2019s son, which was in the court of the prison, and they let Jeremiah
        down with ropes. And in the dungeon there  was no water, but mire. So Jeremiah
        sank in the mire."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Ebed-Melech the Ethiopian, one of the eunuchs, who was in the
        king\u2019s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the dungeon. When
        the king was sitting at the Gate of Benjamin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ebed-Melech went out of the king\u2019s house and spoke to the king,
        saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they
        have done to Jeremiah the prophet, whom they have cast into the dungeon,
        and he is likely to die from hunger in the place where he is. For there 
        is  no more bread in the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king commanded Ebed-Melech the Ethiopian, saying, \u201CTake
        from here thirty men with you, and lift Jeremiah the prophet out of the dungeon
        before he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Ebed-Melech took the men with him and went into the house of the
        king under the treasury, and took from there old clothes and old rags, and
        let them down by ropes into the dungeon to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Ebed-Melech the Ethiopian said to Jeremiah, \u201CPlease put
        these old clothes and rags under your armpits, under the ropes.\u201D And
        Jeremiah did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Zedekiah\u2019s Fears and Jeremiah\u2019s Advice"
      title: "Zedekiah\u2019s Fears and Jeremiah\u2019s Advice"
      number: 13
      content: So they pulled Jeremiah up with ropes and lifted him out of the dungeon.
        And Jeremiah remained in the court of the prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Zedekiah the king sent and had Jeremiah the prophet brought
        to him at the third entrance of the house of the Lord. And the king said
        to Jeremiah, \u201CI will ask you something. Hide nothing from me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CIf I declare it to you, will you
        not surely put me to death? And if I give you advice, you will not listen
        to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Zedekiah the king swore secretly to Jeremiah, saying, \u201CAs
        the Lord lives, who made our very souls, I will not put you to death, nor
        will I give you into the hand of these men who seek your life.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God
        of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018If you surely surrender to the king of
        Babylon\u2019s princes, then your soul shall live; this city shall not be
        burned with fire, and you and your house shall live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if you do not surrender to the king of Babylon\u2019s princes,
        then this city shall be given into the hand of the Chaldeans; they shall
        burn it with fire, and you shall not escape from their hand.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Zedekiah the king said to Jeremiah, \u201CI am afraid of the
        Jews who have defected to the Chaldeans, lest they deliver me into their
        hand, and they abuse me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Jeremiah said, \u201CThey shall not deliver you. Please, obey
        the voice of the Lord which I speak to you. So it shall be well with you,
        and your soul shall live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if you refuse to surrender, this is the word that the Lord has
        shown me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018Now behold, all the women who are left in the king of Judah\u2019s
        house shall  be surrendered to the king of Babylon\u2019s princes, and those
        women shall say:\u201CYour close friends have set upon youAnd prevailed against
        you;Your feet have sunk in the mire,And they have turned away again.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u2018So they shall surrender all your wives and children to the
        Chaldeans. You shall not escape from their hand, but shall be taken by the
        hand of the king of Babylon. And you shall cause this city to be burned with
        fire.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CLet no one know of these words,
        and you shall not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if the princes hear that I have talked with you, and they come
        to you and say to you, \u2018Declare to us now what you have said to the
        king, and also what the king said to you; do not hide it from us, and we
        will not put you to death,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then you shall say to them, \u2018I presented my request before the
        king, that he would not make me return to Jonathan\u2019s house to die there.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then all the princes came to Jeremiah and asked him. And he told
        them according to all these words that the king had commanded. So they stopped
        speaking with him, for the conversation had not been heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Now Jeremiah remained in the court of the prison until the day that
        Jerusalem was taken. And he was there when Jerusalem was taken.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month,
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army came against Jerusalem, and
        besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: In the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, on the ninth
        day of the month, the city was penetrated.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then all the princes of the king of Babylon came in and sat in the
        Middle Gate: Nergal-Sharezer, Samgar-Nebo, Sarsechim, Rabsaris, Nergal-Sarezer,
        Rabmag, with the rest of the princes of the king of Babylon.'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So it was, when Zedekiah the king of Judah and all the men of war
        saw them, that they fled and went out of the city by night, by way of the
        king\u2019s garden, by the gate between the two walls. And he went out by
        way of the plain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Chaldean army pursued them and overtook Zedekiah in the plains
        of Jericho. And when they had captured him, they brought him up to Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, to Riblah in the land of Hamath, where he pronounced judgment
        on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes
        in Riblah; the king of Babylon also killed all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Moreover he put out Zedekiah\u2019s eyes, and bound him with bronze
        fetters to carry him off to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Chaldeans burned the king\u2019s house and the houses of
        the people with fire, and broke down the walls of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive to
        Babylon the remnant of the people who remained in the city and those who
        defected to him, with the rest of the people who remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Goes Free'
      title: Jeremiah Goes Free
      number: 10
      content: But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left in the land of Judah
        the poor people, who had nothing, and gave them vineyards and fields at the
        same time.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon gave charge concerning Jeremiah
        to Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTake him and look after him, and do him no harm; but do to
        him just as he says to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard sent Nebushasban, Rabsaris,
        Nergal-Sharezer, Rabmag, and all the king of Babylon\u2019s chief officers; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: then they sent someone  to take Jeremiah from the court of the prison,
        and committed him to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, that
        he should take him home. So he dwelt among the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Meanwhile the word of the Lord had come to Jeremiah while he was
        shut up in the court of the prison, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo and speak to Ebed-Melech the Ethiopian, saying, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u201CBehold, I will bring My
        words upon this city for adversity and not for good, and they shall be performed
        in that day before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But I will deliver you in that day,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cand
        you shall not be given into the hand of the men of whom you are afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For I will surely deliver you, and you shall not fall by the sword;
        but your life shall be as a prize to you, because you have put your trust
        in Me,\u201D says the Lord.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah with Gedaliah the Governor'
      title: Jeremiah with Gedaliah the Governor
      number: 1
      content: The word that came to Jeremiah from the Lord  after Nebuzaradan the
        captain of the guard had let him go from Ramah, when he had taken him bound
        in chains among all who were carried away captive from Jerusalem and Judah,
        who were carried away captive to Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the captain of the guard took Jeremiah and said to him: \u201CThe
        Lord your God has pronounced this doom on this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the Lord has brought it, and has done just as He said. Because
        you people have sinned against the Lord, and not obeyed His voice, therefore
        this thing has come upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And now look, I free you this day from the chains that were on your
        hand. If it seems good to you to come with me to Babylon, come, and I will
        look after you. But if it seems wrong for you to come with me to Babylon,
        remain here. See, all the land is before you; wherever it seems good and
        convenient for you to go, go there.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now while Jeremiah had not yet gone back, Nebuzaradan  said, \u201CGo
        back to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, whom the king of
        Babylon has made governor over the cities of Judah, and dwell with him among
        the people. Or go wherever it seems convenient for you to go.\u201D So the
        captain of the guard gave him rations and a gift and let him go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then Jeremiah went to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, to Mizpah, and dwelt
        with him among the people who were left in the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when all the captains of the armies who were in the fields, they
        and their men, heard that the king of Babylon had made Gedaliah the son of
        Ahikam governor in the land, and had committed to him men, women, children,
        and the poorest of the land who had not been carried away captive to Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "then they came to Gedaliah at Mizpah\u2014Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        Johanan and Jonathan the sons of Kareah, Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, the
        sons of Ephai the Netophathite, and Jezaniah the son of a Maachathite, they
        and their men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, took an oath
        before them and their men, saying, \u201CDo not be afraid to serve the Chaldeans.
        Dwell in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it shall be well with
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As for me, I will indeed dwell at Mizpah and serve the Chaldeans
        who come to us. But you, gather wine and summer fruit and oil, put them in
        your vessels, and dwell in your cities that you have taken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Likewise, when all the Jews who were in Moab, among the Ammonites,
        in Edom, and who were in all the countries, heard that the king of Babylon
        had left a remnant of Judah, and that he had set over them Gedaliah the son
        of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: then all the Jews returned out of all places where they had been driven,
        and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah, and gathered wine and
        summer fruit in abundance.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Moreover Johanan the son of Kareah and all the captains of the forces
        that were in the fields came to Gedaliah at Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and said to him, \u201CDo you certainly know that Baalis the king
        of the Ammonites has sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah to murder you?\u201D
        But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam did not believe them."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah spoke secretly to Gedaliah in Mizpah,
        saying, \u201CLet me go, please, and I will kill Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        and no one will know it. Why should he murder you, so that all the Jews who
        are gathered to you would be scattered, and the remnant in Judah perish?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah,
        \u201CYou shall not do this thing, for you speak falsely concerning Ishmael.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Insurrection Against Gedaliah'
      title: Insurrection Against Gedaliah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the seventh month that Ishmael the son of
        Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, of the royal family and of the officers of
        the king, came with ten men to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at Mizpah. And
        there they ate bread together in Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and the ten men who were with
        him, arose and struck Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, with
        the sword, and killed him whom the king of Babylon had made governor over
        the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Ishmael also struck down all the Jews who were with him, that  is,
        with Gedaliah at Mizpah, and the Chaldeans who were found there, the men
        of war.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it happened, on the second day after he had killed Gedaliah,
        when as yet no one knew it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'that certain men came from Shechem, from Shiloh, and from Samaria,
        eighty men with their beards shaved and their clothes torn, having cut themselves,
        with offerings and incense in their hand, to bring them to the house of the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Ishmael the son of Nethaniah went out from Mizpah to meet them,
        weeping as he went along; and it happened as he met them that he said to
        them, \u201CCome to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So it was, when they came into the midst of the city, that Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah killed them and  cast  them into the midst of a pit,
        he and the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But ten men were found among them who said to Ishmael, \u201CDo not
        kill us, for we have treasures of wheat, barley, oil, and honey in the field.\u201D
        So he desisted and did not kill them among their brethren. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the pit into which Ishmael had cast all the dead bodies of the
        men whom he had slain, because of Gedaliah, was  the same one Asa the king
        had made for fear of Baasha king of Israel. Ishmael the son of Nethaniah
        filled it with the slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ishmael carried away captive all the rest of the people who
        were in Mizpah, the king\u2019s daughters and all the people who remained
        in Mizpah, whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had committed to Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam. And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah carried them away captive
        and departed to go over to the Ammonites."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when Johanan the son of Kareah and all the captains of the forces
        that were with him heard of all the evil that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah
        had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'they took all the men and went to fight with Ishmael the son of Nethaniah;
        and they found him by the great pool that is in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So it was, when all the people who were with Ishmael saw Johanan
        the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces who were with him,
        that they were glad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then all the people whom Ishmael had carried away captive from Mizpah
        turned around and came back, and went to Johanan the son of Kareah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: But Ishmael the son of Nethaniah escaped from Johanan with eight men
        and went to the Ammonites.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the captains of the forces
        that were with him, took from Mizpah all the rest of the people whom he had
        recovered from Ishmael the son of Nethaniah after he had murdered Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam\u2014the mighty men of war and the women and the children
        and the eunuchs, whom he had brought back from Gibeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they departed and dwelt in the habitation of Chimham, which is
        near Bethlehem, as they went on their way to Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: because of the Chaldeans; for they were afraid of them, because Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah had murdered Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, whom the king
        of Babylon had made governor in the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flight to Egypt Forbidden'
      title: The Flight to Egypt Forbidden
      number: 1
      content: 'Now all the captains of the forces, Johanan the son of Kareah, Jezaniah
        the son of Hoshaiah, and all the people, from the least to the greatest,
        came near '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to Jeremiah the prophet, \u201CPlease, let our petition
        be acceptable to you, and pray for us to the Lord your God, for all this
        remnant (since we are left but  a few of many, as you can see), "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "that the Lord your God may show us the way in which we should walk
        and the thing we should do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jeremiah the prophet said to them, \u201CI have heard. Indeed,
        I will pray to the Lord your God according to your words, and it shall be,
        that  whatever the Lord answers you, I will declare it to you. I will keep
        nothing back from you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So they said to Jeremiah, \u201CLet the Lord be a true and faithful
        witness between us, if we do not do according to everything which the Lord
        your God sends us by you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whether it  is pleasing or displeasing, we will obey the voice of
        the Lord our God to whom we send you, that it may be well with us when we
        obey the voice of the Lord our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And it happened after ten days that the word of the Lord came to
        Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he called Johanan the son of Kareah, all the captains of the
        forces which were with him, and all the people from the least even to the
        greatest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, to
        whom you sent me to present your petition before Him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018If you will still remain in this land, then I will build you
        and not pull you down, and I will plant you and not pluck you up. For I relent
        concerning the disaster that I have brought upon you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Do not be afraid of the king of Babylon, of whom you are afraid;
        do not be afraid of him,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018for I am with you, to
        save you and deliver you from his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And I will show you mercy, that he may have mercy on you and cause
        you to return to your own land.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut if you say, \u2018We will not dwell in this land,\u2019
        disobeying the voice of the Lord your God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u2018No, but we will go to the land of Egypt where we shall
        see no war, nor hear the sound of the trumpet, nor be hungry for bread, and
        there we will dwell\u2019\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then hear now the word of the Lord, O remnant of Judah! Thus says
        the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018If you wholly set your faces
        to enter Egypt, and go to dwell there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then it shall be that the sword which you feared shall overtake you
        there in the land of Egypt; the famine of which you were afraid shall follow
        close after you there in Egypt; and there you shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So shall it be with all the men who set their faces to go to Egypt
        to dwell there. They shall die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence.
        And none of them shall remain or escape from the disaster that I will bring
        upon them.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018As
        My anger and My fury have been poured out on the inhabitants of Jerusalem,
        so will My fury be poured out on you when you enter Egypt. And you shall
        be an oath, an astonishment, a curse, and a reproach; and you shall see this
        place no more.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has said concerning you, O remnant of Judah, \u2018Do
        not go to Egypt!\u2019 Know certainly that I have admonished you this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For you were hypocrites in your hearts when you sent me to the Lord
        your God, saying, \u2018Pray for us to the Lord our God, and according to
        all that the Lord your God says, so declare to us and we will do it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I have this day declared it to you, but you have not obeyed the
        voice of the Lord your God, or anything which He has sent you by me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now therefore, know certainly that you shall die by the sword, by
        famine, and by pestilence in the place where you desire to go to dwell.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt'
      title: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it happened, when Jeremiah had stopped speaking to all the people
        all the words of the Lord their God, for which the Lord their God had sent
        him to them, all these words, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that Azariah the son of Hoshaiah, Johanan the son of Kareah, and
        all the proud men spoke, saying to Jeremiah, \u201CYou speak falsely! The
        Lord our God has not sent you to say, \u2018Do not go to Egypt to dwell there.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Baruch the son of Neriah has set you against us, to deliver us
        into the hand of the Chaldeans, that they may put us to death or carry us
        away captive to Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Johanan the son of Kareah, all the captains of the forces, and
        all the people would not obey the voice of the Lord, to remain in the land
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Johanan the son of Kareah and all the captains of the forces
        took all the remnant of Judah who had returned to dwell in the land of Judah,
        from all nations where they had been driven\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "men, women, children, the king\u2019s daughters, and every person
        whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had left with Gedaliah the son
        of Ahikam, the son of Shaphan, and Jeremiah the prophet and Baruch the son
        of Neriah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: So they went to the land of Egypt, for they did not obey the voice
        of the Lord. And they went as far as Tahpanhes.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Jeremiah in Tahpanhes, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTake large stones in your hand, and hide them in the sight
        of the men of Judah, in the clay in the brick courtyard which is at the entrance
        to Pharaoh\u2019s house in Tahpanhes; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u201CBehold, I will send and bring Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, My
        servant, and will set his throne above these stones that I have hidden. And
        he will spread his royal pavilion over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When he comes, he shall strike the land of Egypt and  deliver to
        death those  appointed for death, and to captivity those  appointed for captivity,
        and to the sword those  appointed for the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will kindle a fire in the houses of the gods of Egypt, and he shall
        burn them and carry them away captive. And he shall array himself with the
        land of Egypt, as a shepherd puts on his garment, and he shall go out from
        there in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He shall also break the sacred pillars of Beth Shemesh that are in
        the land of Egypt; and the houses of the gods of the Egyptians he shall burn
        with fire.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israelites Will Be Punished in Egypt'
      title: Israelites Will Be Punished in Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Jews who dwell
        in the land of Egypt, who dwell at Migdol, at Tahpanhes, at Noph, and in
        the country of Pathros, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018You have
        seen all the calamity that I have brought on Jerusalem and on all the cities
        of Judah; and behold, this day they are  a desolation, and no one dwells
        in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because of their wickedness which they have committed to provoke
        Me to anger, in that they went to burn incense and to serve other gods whom
        they did not know, they nor you nor your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "However I have sent to you all My servants the prophets, rising early
        and sending them, saying, \u201COh, do not do this abominable thing that
        I hate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But they did not listen or incline their ear to turn from their wickedness,
        to burn no incense to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So My fury and My anger were poured out and kindled in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem; and they are wasted and desolate,
        as it is this day.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, thus says the Lord, the God of hosts, the God
        of Israel: \u2018Why do you commit this great evil against yourselves, to
        cut off from you man and woman, child and infant, out of Judah, leaving none
        to remain, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'in that you provoke Me to wrath with the works of your hands, burning
        incense to other gods in the land of Egypt where you have gone to dwell,
        that you may cut yourselves off and be a curse and a reproach among all the
        nations of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you forgotten the wickedness of your fathers, the wickedness
        of the kings of Judah, the wickedness of their wives, your own wickedness,
        and the wickedness of your wives, which they committed in the land of Judah
        and in the streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They have not been humbled, to this day, nor have they feared; they
        have not walked in My law or in My statutes that I set before you and your
        fathers.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: \u2018Behold,
        I will set My face against you for catastrophe and for cutting off all Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will take the remnant of Judah who have set their faces to
        go into the land of Egypt to dwell there, and they shall all be consumed
        and fall in the land of Egypt. They shall be consumed by the sword and by
        famine. They shall die, from the least to the greatest, by the sword and
        by famine; and they shall be an oath, an astonishment, a curse and a reproach! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I will punish those who dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have
        punished Jerusalem, by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "so that none of the remnant of Judah who have gone into the land
        of Egypt to dwell there shall escape or survive, lest they return to the
        land of Judah, to which they desire to return and dwell. For none shall return
        except those who escape.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then all the men who knew that their wives had burned incense to
        other gods, with all the women who stood by, a great multitude, and all the
        people who dwelt in the land of Egypt, in Pathros, answered Jeremiah, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAs  for the word that you have spoken to us in the name of
        the Lord, we will not listen to you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But we will certainly do whatever has gone out of our own mouth,
        to burn incense to the queen of heaven and pour out drink offerings to her,
        as we have done, we and our fathers, our kings and our princes, in the cities
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem. For then we had plenty of food,
        were well-off, and saw no trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But since we stopped burning incense to the queen of heaven and pouring
        out drink offerings to her, we have lacked everything and have been consumed
        by the sword and by famine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The  women  also  said,  \u201CAnd when we burned incense to the
        queen of heaven and poured out drink offerings to her, did we make cakes
        for her, to worship her, and pour out drink offerings to her without our
        husbands\u2019 permission?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to all the people\u2014the men, the women, and
        all the people who had given him that answer\u2014saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThe incense that you burned in the cities of Judah and in the
        streets of Jerusalem, you and your fathers, your kings and your princes,
        and the people of the land, did not the Lord remember them, and did it not
        come into His mind? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the Lord could no longer bear it, because of the evil of your
        doings and because of the abominations which you committed. Therefore your
        land is a desolation, an astonishment, a curse, and without an inhabitant,
        as it  is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Because you have burned incense and because you have sinned against
        the Lord, and have not obeyed the voice of the Lord or walked in His law,
        in His statutes or in His testimonies, therefore this calamity has happened
        to you, as at this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Moreover Jeremiah said to all the people and to all the women, \u201CHear
        the word of the Lord, all Judah who are in the land of Egypt! "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, saying: \u2018You
        and your wives have spoken with your mouths and fulfilled with your hands,
        saying, \u201CWe will surely keep our vows that we have made, to burn incense
        to the queen of heaven and pour out drink offerings to her.\u201D You will
        surely keep your vows and perform your vows!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore hear the word of the Lord, all Judah who dwell in the land
        of Egypt: \u2018Behold, I have sworn by My great name,\u2019 says the Lord,
        \u2018that My name shall no more be named in the mouth of any man of Judah
        in all the land of Egypt, saying, \u201CThe Lord God lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Behold, I will watch over them for adversity and not for good. And
        all the men of Judah who are in the land of Egypt shall be consumed by the
        sword and by famine, until there is an end to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yet a small number who escape the sword shall return from the land
        of Egypt to the land of Judah; and all the remnant of Judah, who have gone
        to the land of Egypt to dwell there, shall know whose words will stand, Mine
        or theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And this shall  be a sign to you,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018that
        I will punish you in this place, that you may know that My words will surely
        stand against you for adversity.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will give Pharaoh Hophra
        king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies and into the hand of those who
        seek his life, as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, his enemy who sought his life.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Assurance to Baruch'
      title: Assurance to Baruch
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Neriah,
        when he had written these words in a book at the instruction of Jeremiah,
        in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel, to you, O Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018You said, \u201CWoe is me now! For the Lord has added grief
        to my sorrow. I fainted in my sighing, and I find no rest.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThus you shall say to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold,
        what I have built I will break down, and what I have planted I will pluck
        up, that is, this whole land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And do you seek great things for yourself? Do not seek them; for
        behold, I will bring adversity on all flesh,\u201D says the Lord. \u201CBut
        I will give your life to you as a prize in all places, wherever you go.\u201D
        \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Egypt'
      title: Judgment on Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'The word of the Lord which came to Jeremiah the prophet against the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Against Egypt.Concerning the army of Pharaoh Necho, king of Egypt,
        which was by the River Euphrates in Carchemish, and which Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon defeated in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah:'
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201COrder the buckler and shield,And draw near to battle!"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Harness the horses,And mount up, you horsemen!Stand forth with your
        helmets,Polish the spears,Put on the armor!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Why have I seen them dismayed and turned back?Their mighty ones are
        beaten down;They have speedily fled,And did not look back,For  fear was all
        around,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CDo not let the swift flee away,Nor the mighty man escape;They
        will stumble and fallToward the north, by the River Euphrates."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWho is this coming up like a flood,Whose waters move like the
        rivers?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Egypt rises up like a flood,And its waters move like the rivers;And
        he says, \u2018I will go up and cover the earth,I will destroy the city and
        its inhabitants.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Come up, O horses, and rage, O chariots!And let the mighty men come
        forth:The Ethiopians and the Libyans who handle the shield,And the Lydians
        who handle and bend the bow.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: For this is  the day of the Lord God of hosts,A day of vengeance,That
        He may avenge Himself on His adversaries.The sword shall devour;It shall
        be satiated and made drunk with their blood;For the Lord God of hosts has
        a sacrificeIn the north country by the River Euphrates.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CGo up to Gilead and take balm,O virgin, the daughter of Egypt;In
        vain you will use many medicines;You shall not be cured."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Babylonia Will Strike Egypt'
      title: Babylonia Will Strike Egypt
      number: 12
      content: "The nations have heard of your shame,And your cry has filled the
        land;For the mighty man has stumbled against the mighty;They both have fallen
        together.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The word that the Lord spoke to Jeremiah the prophet, how Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon would come and  strike the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDeclare in Egypt, and proclaim in Migdol;Proclaim in Noph and
        in Tahpanhes;Say, \u2018Stand fast and prepare yourselves,For the sword devours
        all around you.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Why are your valiant men swept away?They did not standBecause the
        Lord drove them away.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He made many fall;Yes, one fell upon another.And they said, \u2018Arise!Let
        us go back to our own peopleAnd to the land of our nativityFrom the oppressing
        sword.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They cried there,\u2018Pharaoh, king of Egypt, is  but a noise.He
        has passed by the appointed time!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAs I live,\u201D says the King,Whose name is the Lord of hosts,\u201CSurely
        as Tabor is among the mountainsAnd as Carmel by the sea, so he shall come."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: O you daughter dwelling in Egypt,Prepare yourself to go into captivity!For
        Noph shall be waste and desolate, without inhabitant.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CEgypt is a very pretty heifer,But destruction comes, it comes
        from the north."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Also her mercenaries are in her midst like fat bulls,For they also
        are turned back,They have fled away together.They did not stand,For the day
        of their calamity had come upon them,The time of their punishment.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Her noise shall go like a serpent,For they shall march with an armyAnd
        come against her with axes,Like those who chop wood.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThey shall cut down her forest,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThough
        it cannot be searched,Because they are innumerable,And more numerous than
        grasshoppers."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The daughter of Egypt shall be ashamed;She shall be delivered into
        the handOf the people of the north.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, says: \u201CBehold, I will
        bring punishment on Amon of No, and Pharaoh and Egypt, with their gods and
        their kings\u2014Pharaoh and those who trust in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: God Will Preserve Israel'
      title: God Will Preserve Israel
      number: 26
      content: "And I will deliver them into the hand of those who seek their lives,
        into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and the hand of his servants.
        Afterward it shall be inhabited as in the days of old,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut do not fear, O My servant Jacob,And do not be dismayed,
        O Israel!For behold, I will save you from afar,And your offspring from the
        land of their captivity;Jacob shall return, have rest and be at ease;No one
        shall make him afraid."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do not fear, O Jacob My servant,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CFor I
        am with you;For I will make a complete end of all the nationsTo which I have
        driven you,But I will not make a complete end of you.I will rightly correct
        you,For I will not leave you wholly unpunished.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Philistia'
      title: Judgment on Philistia
      number: 1
      content: The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet against the
        Philistines, before Pharaoh attacked Gaza.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, waters rise out of the north,And
        shall be an overflowing flood;They shall overflow the land and all that is
        in it,The city and those who dwell within;Then the men shall cry,And all
        the inhabitants of the land shall wail."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: At the noise of the stamping hooves of his strong horses,At the rushing
        of his chariots,At the rumbling of his wheels,The fathers will not look back
        for their children,Lacking courage,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Because of the day that comes to plunder all the Philistines,To cut
        off from Tyre and Sidon every helper who remains;For the Lord shall plunder
        the Philistines,The remnant of the country of Caphtor.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Baldness has come upon Gaza,Ashkelon is cut offWith the remnant of
        their valley.How long will you cut yourself?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO you sword of the Lord,How long until you are quiet?Put yourself
        up into your scabbard,Rest and be still!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How can it be quiet,Seeing the Lord has given it a chargeAgainst
        Ashkelon and against the seashore?There He has appointed it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Moab'
      title: Judgment on Moab
      number: 1
      content: "Against Moab.Thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel:\u201CWoe
        to Nebo!For it is plundered,Kirjathaim is shamed and taken;The high stronghold
        is shamed and dismayed\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "No more praise of Moab.In Heshbon they have devised evil against
        her:\u2018Come, and let us cut her off as a nation.\u2019You also shall be
        cut down, O Madmen!The sword shall pursue you;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A voice of crying shall  be from Horonaim:\u2018Plundering and great
        destruction!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CMoab is destroyed;Her little ones have caused a cry to be heard;"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For in the Ascent of Luhith they ascend with continual weeping;For
        in the descent of Horonaim the enemies have heard a cry of destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CFlee, save your lives!And be like the juniper in the wilderness."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For because you have trusted in your works and your treasures,You
        also shall be taken.And Chemosh shall go forth into captivity,His priests
        and his princes together.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And the plunderer shall come against every city;No one shall escape.The
        valley also shall perish,And the plain shall be destroyed,As the Lord has
        spoken.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CGive wings to Moab,That she may flee and get away;For her cities
        shall be desolate,Without any to dwell in them."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Cursed is he who does the work of the Lord deceitfully,And cursed
        is he who keeps back his sword from blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CMoab has been at ease from his youth;He has settled on his
        dregs,And has not been emptied from vessel to vessel,Nor has he gone into
        captivity.Therefore his taste remained in him,And his scent has not changed."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat
        I shall send him wine-workersWho will tip him overAnd empty his vesselsAnd
        break the bottles."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Moab shall be ashamed of Chemosh,As the house of Israel was ashamed
        of Bethel, their confidence.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHow can you say, \u2018We are mightyAnd strong men for the
        war\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moab is plundered and gone up from her cities;Her chosen young men
        have gone down to the slaughter,\u201D says the King,Whose name is the Lord
        of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThe calamity of Moab is near at hand,And his affliction comes
        quickly."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Bemoan him, all you who are around him;And all you who know his name,Say,
        \u2018How the strong staff is broken,The beautiful rod!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CO daughter inhabiting Dibon,Come down from your glory,And sit
        in thirst;For the plunderer of Moab has come against you,He has destroyed
        your strongholds."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "O inhabitant of Aroer,Stand by the way and watch;Ask him who fleesAnd
        her who escapes;Say, \u2018What has happened?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Moab is shamed, for he is broken down.Wail and cry!Tell it in Arnon,
        that Moab is plundered.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd judgment has come on the plain country:On Holon and Jahzah
        and Mephaath,"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: On Dibon and Nebo and Beth Diblathaim,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: On Kirjathaim and Beth Gamul and Beth Meon,
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: On Kerioth and Bozrah,On all the cities of the land of Moab,Far or
        near.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The horn of Moab is cut off,And his arm is broken,\u201D says the
        Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CMake him drunk,Because he exalted himself against the Lord.Moab
        shall wallow in his vomit,And he shall also be in derision."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For was not Israel a derision to you?Was he found among thieves?For
        whenever you speak of him,You shake your  head  in  scorn.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You who dwell in Moab,Leave the cities and dwell in the rock,And
        be like the dove which makes her nestIn the sides of the cave\u2019s mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWe have heard the pride of Moab(He is exceedingly proud),Of
        his loftiness and arrogance and pride,And of the haughtiness of his heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CI know his wrath,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CBut it is not right;His
        lies have made nothing right."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Therefore I will wail for Moab,And I will cry out for all Moab;I will
        mourn for the men of Kir Heres.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: O vine of Sibmah! I will weep for you with the weeping of Jazer.Your
        plants have gone over the sea,They reach to the sea of Jazer.The plunderer
        has fallen on your summer fruit and your vintage.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Joy and gladness are takenFrom the plentiful fieldAnd from the land
        of Moab;I have caused wine to fail from the winepresses;No one will tread
        with joyous shouting\u2014Not joyous shouting!"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CFrom the cry of Heshbon to Elealeh and to JahazThey have uttered
        their voice,From Zoar to Horonaim,Like a three-year-old heifer;For the waters
        of Nimrim also shall be desolate."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CMoreover,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CI will cause to cease in
        MoabThe one who offers sacrifices in the high placesAnd burns incense to
        his gods."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Therefore My heart shall wail like flutes for Moab,And like flutes
        My heart shall wailFor the men of Kir Heres.Therefore the riches they have
        acquired have perished.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CFor every head shall  be bald, and every beard clipped;On all
        the hands shall  be cuts, and on the loins sackcloth\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "A general lamentationOn all the housetops of Moab,And in its streets;For
        I have broken Moab like a vessel in which is no pleasure,\u201D says the
        Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CThey shall wail:\u2018How she is broken down!How Moab has turned
        her back with shame!\u2019So Moab shall be a derisionAnd a dismay to all
        those about her.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, one shall fly like an eagle,And
        spread his wings over Moab."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Kerioth is taken,And the strongholds are surprised;The mighty men\u2019s
        hearts in Moab on that day shall beLike the heart of a woman in birth pangs."
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And Moab shall be destroyed as a people,Because he exalted himself
        against the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Fear and the pit and the snare shall  be upon you,O inhabitant of
        Moab,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CHe who flees from the fear shall fall into the pit,And he who
        gets out of the pit shall be caught in the snare.For upon Moab, upon it I
        will bringThe year of their punishment,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CThose who fled stood under the shadow of HeshbonBecause of
        exhaustion.But a fire shall come out of Heshbon,A flame from the midst of
        Sihon,And shall devour the brow of Moab,The crown of the head of the sons
        of tumult."
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: Woe to you, O Moab!The people of Chemosh perish;For your sons have
        been taken captive,And your daughters captive.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CYet I will bring back the captives of MoabIn the latter days,\u201D
        says the Lord.Thus far is the judgment of Moab."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Ammon'
      title: Judgment on Ammon
      number: 1
      content: "Against the Ammonites.Thus says the Lord:\u201CHas Israel no sons?Has
        he no heir?Why then does Milcom inherit Gad,And his people dwell in its cities?"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat
        I will cause to be heard an alarm of warIn Rabbah of the Ammonites;It shall
        be a desolate mound,And her villages shall be burned with fire.Then Israel
        shall take possession of his inheritance,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CWail, O Heshbon, for Ai is plundered!Cry, you daughters of
        Rabbah,Gird yourselves with sackcloth!Lament and run to and fro by the walls;For
        Milcom shall go into captivityWith his priests and his princes together."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Why do you boast in the valleys,Your flowing valley, O backsliding
        daughter?Who trusted in her treasures, saying,\u2018Who will come against
        me?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Behold, I will bring fear upon you,\u201DSays the Lord God of hosts,\u201CFrom
        all those who are around you;You shall be driven out, everyone headlong,And
        no one will gather those who wander off."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Judgment on Edom'
      title: Judgment on Edom
      number: 6
      content: "But afterward I will bring backThe captives of the people of Ammon,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Against Edom.Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CIs wisdom no more
        in Teman?Has counsel perished from the prudent?Has their wisdom vanished?"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Flee, turn back, dwell in the depths, O inhabitants of Dedan!For I
        will bring the calamity of Esau upon him,The time that I will punish him.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: If grape-gatherers came to you,Would they not leave some gleaning
        grapes?If thieves by night,Would they not destroy until they have enough?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But I have made Esau bare;I have uncovered his secret places,And he
        shall not be able to hide himself.His descendants are plundered,His brethren
        and his neighbors,And he is no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Leave your fatherless children,I will preserve them alive;And let
        your widows trust in Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, those whose judgment was not
        to drink of the cup have assuredly drunk. And are you the one who will altogether
        go unpunished? You shall not go unpunished, but you shall surely drink of 
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I have sworn by Myself,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cthat Bozrah
        shall become a desolation, a reproach, a waste, and a curse. And all its
        cities shall be perpetual wastes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I have heard a message from the Lord,And an ambassador has been sent
        to the nations:\u201CGather together, come against her,And rise up to battle!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CFor indeed, I will make you small among nations,Despised among
        men."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Your fierceness has deceived you,The pride of your heart,O you who
        dwell in the clefts of the rock,Who hold the height of the hill!Though you
        make your nest as high as the eagle,I will bring you down from there,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CEdom also shall be an astonishment;Everyone who goes by it
        will be astonishedAnd will hiss at all its plagues."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "As in the overthrow of Sodom and GomorrahAnd their neighbors,\u201D
        says the Lord,\u201CNo one shall remain there,Nor shall a son of man dwell
        in it."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBehold, he shall come up like a lion from the floodplain of
        the JordanAgainst the dwelling place of the strong;But I will suddenly make
        him run away from her.And who is a chosen man  that I may appoint over her?For
        who is like Me?Who will arraign Me?And who is that shepherdWho will withstand
        Me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Therefore hear the counsel of the Lord that He has taken against Edom,And
        His purposes that He has proposed against the inhabitants of Teman:Surely
        the least of the flock shall draw them out;Surely He shall make their dwelling
        places desolate with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The earth shakes at the noise of their fall;At the cry its noise is
        heard at the Red Sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Judgment on Damascus'
      title: Judgment on Damascus
      number: 22
      content: Behold, He shall come up and fly like the eagle,And spread His wings
        over Bozrah;The heart of the mighty men of Edom in that day shall beLike
        the heart of a woman in birth pangs.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Against Damascus.\u201CHamath and Arpad are shamed,For they have
        heard bad news.They are fainthearted;There  is trouble on the sea;It cannot
        be quiet."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Damascus has grown feeble;She turns to flee,And fear has seized her.Anguish
        and sorrows have taken her like a woman in labor.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Why is the city of praise not deserted, the city of My joy?
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore her young men shall fall in her streets,And all the men
        of war shall be cut off in that day,\u201D says the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Judgment on Kedar and Hazor'
      title: Judgment on Kedar and Hazor
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI will kindle a fire in the wall of Damascus,And it shall consume
        the palaces of Ben-Hadad.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Against Kedar and against the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon shall strike.Thus says the Lord:\u201CArise, go up to Kedar,And
        devastate the men of the East!"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Their tents and their flocks they shall take away.They shall take
        for themselves their curtains,All their vessels and their camels;And they
        shall cry out to them,\u2018Fear is on every side!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CFlee, get far away! Dwell in the depths,O inhabitants of Hazor!\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CFor Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has taken counsel
        against you,And has conceived a plan against you."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CArise, go up to the wealthy nation that dwells securely,\u201D
        says the Lord,\u201CWhich has neither gates nor bars,Dwelling alone."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Their camels shall be for booty,And the multitude of their cattle
        for plunder.I will scatter to all winds those in the farthest corners,And
        I will bring their calamity from all its sides,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Judgment on Elam'
      title: Judgment on Elam
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHazor shall be a dwelling for jackals, a desolation forever;No
        one shall reside there,Nor son of man dwell in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The word of the Lord that came to Jeremiah the prophet against Elam,
        in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts:\u2018Behold, I will break the
        bow of Elam,The foremost of their might."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Against Elam I will bring the four windsFrom the four quarters of
        heaven,And scatter them toward all those winds;There shall be no nations
        where the outcasts of Elam will not go.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For I will cause Elam to be dismayed before their enemiesAnd before
        those who seek their life.I will bring disaster upon them,My fierce anger,\u2019
        says the Lord;\u2018And I will send the sword after themUntil I have consumed
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "I will set My throne in Elam,And will destroy from there the king
        and the princes,\u2019 says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u2018But it shall come to pass in the latter days:I will bring back
        the captives of Elam,\u2019 says the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Babylon and Babylonia'
      title: Judgment on Babylon and Babylonia
      number: 1
      content: The word that the Lord spoke against Babylon and against the land
        of the Chaldeans by Jeremiah the prophet.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDeclare among the nations,Proclaim, and set up a standard;Proclaim\u2014do
        not conceal it\u2014Say, \u2018Babylon is taken, Bel is shamed.Merodach is
        broken in pieces;Her idols are humiliated,Her images are broken in pieces.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For out of the north a nation comes up against her,Which shall make
        her land desolate,And no one shall dwell therein.They shall move, they shall
        depart,Both man and beast.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIn those days and in that time,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThe
        children of Israel shall come,They and the children of Judah together;With
        continual weeping they shall come,And seek the Lord their God."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They shall ask the way to Zion,With their faces toward it, saying,\u2018Come
        and let us join ourselves to the LordIn  a perpetual covenantThat will not
        be forgotten.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMy people have been lost sheep.Their shepherds have led them
        astray;They have turned them away on  the mountains.They have gone from mountain
        to hill;They have forgotten their resting place."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All who found them have devoured them;And their adversaries said,
        \u2018We have not offended,Because they have sinned against the Lord, the
        habitation of justice,The Lord, the hope of their fathers.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CMove from the midst of Babylon,Go out of the land of the Chaldeans;And
        be like the rams before the flocks."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For behold, I will raise and cause to come up against BabylonAn assembly
        of great nations from the north country,And they shall array themselves against
        her;From there she shall be captured.Their arrows shall  be like those of
        an expert warrior;None shall return in vain.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Chaldea shall become plunder;All who plunder her shall be satisfied,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause you were glad, because you rejoiced,You destroyers
        of My heritage,Because you have grown fat like a heifer threshing grain,And
        you bellow like bulls,"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Your mother shall be deeply ashamed;She who bore you shall be ashamed.Behold,
        the least of the nations shall  be a wilderness,A dry land and a desert.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Because of the wrath of the LordShe shall not be inhabited,But she
        shall be wholly desolate.Everyone who goes by Babylon shall be horrifiedAnd
        hiss at all her plagues.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CPut yourselves in array against Babylon all around,All you
        who bend the bow;Shoot at her, spare no arrows,For she has sinned against
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Shout against her all around;She has given her hand,Her foundations
        have fallen,Her walls are thrown down;For it is the vengeance of the Lord.Take
        vengeance on her.As she has done, so do to her.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Cut off the sower from Babylon,And him who handles the sickle at harvest
        time.For fear of the oppressing swordEveryone shall turn to his own people,And
        everyone shall flee to his own land.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIsrael is like scattered sheep;The lions have driven him away.First
        the king of Assyria devoured him;Now at last this Nebuchadnezzar king of
        Babylon has broken his bones.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel:\u201CBehold,
        I will punish the king of Babylon and his land,As I have punished the king
        of Assyria."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: But I will bring back Israel to his home,And he shall feed on Carmel
        and Bashan;His soul shall be satisfied on Mount Ephraim and Gilead.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In those days and in that time,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThe iniquity
        of Israel shall be sought, but there  shall  be none;And the sins of Judah,
        but they shall not be found;For I will pardon those whom I preserve."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo up against the land of Merathaim, against it,And against
        the inhabitants of Pekod.Waste and utterly destroy them,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAnd
        do according to all that I have commanded you."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A sound of battle is in the land,And of great destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: How the hammer of the whole earth has been cut apart and broken!How
        Babylon has become a desolation among the nations!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: I have laid a snare for you;You have indeed been trapped, O Babylon,And
        you were not aware;You have been found and also caught,Because you have contended
        against the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The Lord has opened His armory,And has brought out the weapons of
        His indignation;For this is the work of the Lord God of hostsIn the land
        of the Chaldeans.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Come against her from the farthest border;Open her storehouses;Cast
        her up as heaps of ruins,And destroy her utterly;Let nothing of her be left.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Slay all her bulls,Let them go down to the slaughter.Woe to them!For
        their day has come, the time of their punishment.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The voice of those who flee and escape from the land of BabylonDeclares
        in Zion the vengeance of the Lord our God,The vengeance of His temple.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCall together the archers against Babylon.All you who bend
        the bow, encamp against it all around;Let none of them escape.Repay her according
        to her work;According to all she has done, do to her;For she has been proud
        against the Lord,Against the Holy One of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore her young men shall fall in the streets,And all her men
        of war shall be cut off in that day,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you,O most haughty one!\u201D says the
        Lord God of hosts;\u201CFor your day has come,The time that I will punish
        you."
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The most proud shall stumble and fall,And no one will raise him up;I
        will kindle a fire in his cities,And it will devour all around him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CThe children of Israel were oppressed,Along
        with the children of Judah;All who took them captive have held them fast;They
        have refused to let them go."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Their Redeemer is strong;The Lord of hosts is His name.He will thoroughly
        plead their case,That He may give rest to the land,And disquiet the inhabitants
        of Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CA sword is against the Chaldeans,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CAgainst
        the inhabitants of Babylon,And against her princes and her wise men."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: A sword is  against the soothsayers, and they will be fools.A sword
        is against her mighty men, and they will be dismayed.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: A sword is against their horses,Against their chariots,And against
        all the mixed peoples who are in her midst;And they will become like women.A
        sword is against her treasures, and they will be robbed.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: A drought is against her waters, and they will be dried up.For it
        is the land of carved images,And they are insane with their idols.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CTherefore the wild desert beasts shall dwell there with the
        jackals,And the ostriches shall dwell in it.It shall be inhabited no more
        forever,Nor shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "As God overthrew Sodom and GomorrahAnd their neighbors,\u201D says
        the Lord,\u201CSo no one shall reside there,Nor son of man dwell in it."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CBehold, a people shall come from the north,And a great nation
        and many kingsShall be raised up from the ends of the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: They shall hold the bow and the lance;They are cruel and shall not
        show mercy.Their voice shall roar like the sea;They shall ride on horses,Set
        in array, like a man for the battle,Against you, O daughter of Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "\u201CThe king of Babylon has heard the report about them,And his
        hands grow feeble;Anguish has taken hold of him,Pangs as of a woman in childbirth."
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CBehold, he shall come up like a lion from the floodplain of
        the JordanAgainst the dwelling place of the strong;But I will make them suddenly
        run away from her.And who is a chosen man  that I may appoint over her?For
        who is like Me?Who will arraign Me?And who is that shepherdWho will withstand
        Me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Therefore hear the counsel of the Lord that He has taken against Babylon,And
        His purposes that He has proposed against the land of the Chaldeans:Surely
        the least of the flock shall draw them out;Surely He will make their dwelling
        place desolate with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: At the noise of the taking of BabylonThe earth trembles,And the cry
        is heard among the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Utter Destruction of Babylon'
      title: The Utter Destruction of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I will raise up against Babylon,Against
        those who dwell in Leb Kamai,A destroying wind."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And I will send winnowers to Babylon,Who shall winnow her and empty
        her land.For in the day of doomThey shall be against her all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Against her  let the archer bend his bow,And lift himself up against
        her in his armor.Do not spare her young men;Utterly destroy all her army.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Thus the slain shall fall in the land of the Chaldeans,And those thrust
        through in her streets.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For Israel is not forsaken, nor Judah,By his God, the Lord of hosts,Though
        their land was filled with sin against the Holy One of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Flee from the midst of Babylon,And every one save his life!Do not
        be cut off in her iniquity,For this is the time of the Lord\u2019s vengeance;He
        shall recompense her."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Babylon was a golden cup in the Lord\u2019s hand,That made all the
        earth drunk.The nations drank her wine;Therefore the nations are deranged."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Babylon has suddenly fallen and been destroyed.Wail for her!Take balm
        for her pain;Perhaps she may be healed.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: We would have healed Babylon,But she is not healed.Forsake her, and
        let us go everyone to his own country;For her judgment reaches to heaven
        and is lifted up to the skies.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The Lord has revealed our righteousness.Come and let us declare in
        Zion the work of the Lord our God.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Make the arrows bright!Gather the shields!The Lord has raised up the
        spirit of the kings of the Medes.For His plan is against Babylon to destroy
        it,Because it is  the vengeance of the Lord,The vengeance for His temple.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Set up the standard on the walls of Babylon;Make the guard strong,Set
        up the watchmen,Prepare the ambushes.For the Lord has both devised and doneWhat
        He spoke against the inhabitants of Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: O you who dwell by many waters,Abundant in treasures,Your end has
        come,The measure of your covetousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord of hosts has sworn by Himself:\u201CSurely I will fill you
        with men, as with locusts,And they shall lift up a shout against you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He has made the earth by His power;He has established the world by
        His wisdom,And stretched out the heaven by His understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When He utters His voice\u2014There  is a multitude of waters in
        the heavens:\u201CHe causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth;He
        makes lightnings for the rain;He brings the wind out of His treasuries.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Everyone is dull-hearted, without knowledge;Every metalsmith is put
        to shame by the carved image;For his molded image is falsehood,And there 
        is no breath in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They are futile, a work of errors;In the time of their punishment
        they shall perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The Portion of Jacob is not like them,For He is the Maker of all things;And
        Israel  is the tribe of His inheritance.The Lord of hosts is His name.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou  are My battle-ax and weapons of war:For with you I will
        break the nation in pieces;With you I will destroy kingdoms;"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: With you I will break in pieces the horse and its rider;With you I
        will break in pieces the chariot and its rider;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: With you also I will break in pieces man and woman;With you I will
        break in pieces old and young;With you I will break in pieces the young man
        and the maiden;
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: With you also I will break in pieces the shepherd and his flock;With
        you I will break in pieces the farmer and his yoke of oxen;And with you I
        will break in pieces governors and rulers.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd I will repay BabylonAnd all the inhabitants of ChaldeaFor
        all the evil they have doneIn Zion in your sight,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you, O destroying mountain,Who destroys
        all the earth,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CAnd I will stretch out My hand against
        you,Roll you down from the rocks,And make you a burnt mountain."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They shall not take from you a stone for a cornerNor a stone for
        a foundation,But you shall be desolate forever,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Set up a banner in the land,Blow the trumpet among the nations!Prepare
        the nations against her,Call the kingdoms together against her:Ararat, Minni,
        and Ashkenaz.Appoint a general against her;Cause the horses to come up like
        the bristling locusts.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Prepare against her the nations,With the kings of the Medes,Its governors
        and all its rulers,All the land of his dominion.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And the land will tremble and sorrow;For every purpose of the Lord
        shall be performed against Babylon,To make the land of Babylon a desolation
        without inhabitant.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The mighty men of Babylon have ceased fighting,They have remained
        in their strongholds;Their might has failed,They became like women;They have
        burned her dwelling places,The bars of her gate are broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: One runner will run to meet another,And one messenger to meet another,To
        show the king of Babylon that his city is taken on all sides;
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The passages are blocked,The reeds they have burned with fire,And
        the men of war are terrified.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel:\u201CThe daughter
        of Babylon is  like a threshing floorWhen  it is time to thresh her;Yet a
        little whileAnd the time of her harvest will come.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CNebuchadnezzar the king of BabylonHas devoured me, he has crushed
        me;He has made me an empty vessel,He has swallowed me up like a monster;He
        has filled his stomach with my delicacies,He has spit me out."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Let the violence done to me and my flesh be upon Babylon,\u201DThe
        inhabitant of Zion will say;\u201CAnd my blood be upon the inhabitants of
        Chaldea!\u201DJerusalem will say."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord:\u201CBehold, I will plead your case
        and take vengeance for you.I will dry up her sea and make her springs dry."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Babylon shall become a heap,A dwelling place for jackals,An astonishment
        and a hissing,Without an inhabitant.
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "They shall roar together like lions,They shall growl like lions\u2019
        whelps."
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "In their excitement I will prepare their feasts;I will make them
        drunk,That they may rejoice,And sleep a perpetual sleepAnd not awake,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CI will bring them downLike lambs to the slaughter,Like rams
        with male goats."
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201COh, how Sheshach is taken!Oh, how the praise of the whole earth
        is seized!How Babylon has become desolate among the nations!"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: The sea has come up over Babylon;She is covered with the multitude
        of its waves.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Her cities are a desolation,A dry land and a wilderness,A land where
        no one dwells,Through which no son of man passes.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: I will punish Bel in Babylon,And I will bring out of his mouth what
        he has swallowed;And the nations shall not stream to him anymore.Yes, the
        wall of Babylon shall fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CMy people, go out of the midst of her!And let everyone deliver
        himself from the fierce anger of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: And lest your heart faint,And you fear for the rumor that will  be
        heard in the land(A rumor will come one year,And after that, in another yearA
        rumor will  come,And violence in the land,Ruler against ruler),
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Therefore behold, the days are comingThat I will bring judgment on
        the carved images of Babylon;Her whole land shall be ashamed,And all her
        slain shall fall in her midst.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then the heavens and the earth and all that is in themShall sing
        joyously over Babylon;For the plunderers shall come to her from the north,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: As Babylon has  caused the slain of Israel to fall,So at Babylon the
        slain of all the earth shall fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: You who have escaped the sword,Get away! Do not stand still!Remember
        the Lord afar off,And let Jerusalem come to your mind.
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "We are ashamed because we have heard reproach.Shame has covered our
        faces,For strangers have come into the sanctuaries of the Lord\u2019s house."
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CTherefore behold, the days are coming,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat
        I will bring judgment on her carved images,And throughout all her land the
        wounded shall groan."
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Though Babylon were to mount up to heaven,And though she were to
        fortify the height of her strength,Yet from Me plunderers would come to her,\u201D
        says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: The sound of a cry comes from Babylon,And great destruction from the
        land of the Chaldeans,
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: Because the Lord is plundering BabylonAnd silencing her loud voice,Though
        her waves roar like great waters,And the noise of their voice is uttered,
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: Because the plunderer comes against her, against Babylon,And her mighty
        men are taken.Every one of their bows is broken;For the Lord  is the God
        of recompense,He will surely repay.
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "\u201CAnd I will make drunkHer princes and wise men,Her governors,
        her deputies, and her mighty men.And they shall sleep a perpetual sleepAnd
        not awake,\u201D says the King,Whose name is the Lord of hosts."
      comments: []
    - name: "58: Jeremiah\u2019s Command to Seraiah"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Command to Seraiah"
      number: 58
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts:\u201CThe broad walls of Babylon shall
        be utterly broken,And her high gates shall be burned with fire;The people
        will labor in vain,And the nations, because of the fire;And they shall be
        weary.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'The word which Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah the son of
        Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, when he went with Zedekiah the king of Judah
        to Babylon in the fourth year of his reign. And Seraiah was the quartermaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'So Jeremiah wrote in a book all the evil that would come upon Babylon,
        all these words that are written against Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "And Jeremiah said to Seraiah, \u201CWhen you arrive in Babylon and
        see it, and read all these words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "then you shall say, \u2018O Lord, You have spoken against this place
        to cut it off, so that none shall remain in it, neither man nor beast, but
        it shall be desolate forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Now it shall be, when you have finished reading this book, that you
        shall tie a stone to it and throw it out into the Euphrates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "Then you shall say, \u2018Thus Babylon shall sink and not rise from
        the catastrophe that I will bring upon her. And they shall be weary.\u2019
        \u201DThus far are the words of Jeremiah."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem Reviewed'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem Reviewed
      number: 1
      content: "Zedekiah was  twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal the daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He also did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that
        Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For because of the anger of the Lord  this happened in Jerusalem and
        Judah, till He finally cast them out from His presence. Then Zedekiah rebelled
        against the king of Babylon.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth
        month, on the tenth day of the month, that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon
        and all his army came against Jerusalem and encamped against it; and they
        built a siege wall against it all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the city was besieged until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By the fourth month, on the ninth day of the month, the famine had
        become so severe in the city that there was no food for the people of the
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the city wall was broken through, and all the men of war fled
        and went out of the city at night by way of the gate between the two walls,
        which was by the king\u2019s garden, even though the Chaldeans were near
        the city all around. And they went by way of the plain."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king, and they overtook
        Zedekiah in the plains of Jericho. All his army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So they took the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon at
        Riblah in the land of Hamath, and he pronounced judgment on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes.
        And he killed all the princes of Judah in Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Temple and City Plundered and Burned'
      title: The Temple and City Plundered and Burned
      number: 11
      content: He also put out the eyes of Zedekiah; and the king of Babylon bound
        him in bronze fetters, took him to Babylon, and put him in prison till the
        day of his death.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now in the fifth month, on the tenth day of the month (which was
        the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon), Nebuzaradan,
        the captain of the guard, who served the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He burned the house of the Lord and the king\u2019s house; all the
        houses of Jerusalem, that is, all the houses of the great, he burned with
        fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the army of the Chaldeans who were with the captain of the
        guard broke down all the walls of Jerusalem all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive some
        of the poor people, the rest of the people who remained in the city, the
        defectors who had deserted to the king of Babylon, and the rest of the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left some of the poor of
        the land as vinedressers and farmers.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The bronze pillars that were in the house of the Lord, and the carts
        and the bronze Sea that were in the house of the Lord, the Chaldeans broke
        in pieces, and carried all their bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They also took away the pots, the shovels, the trimmers, the bowls,
        the spoons, and all the bronze utensils with which the priests ministered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The basins, the firepans, the bowls, the pots, the lampstands, the
        spoons, and the cups, whatever was solid gold and whatever was solid silver,
        the captain of the guard took away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The two pillars, one Sea, the twelve bronze bulls which were under
        it, and the carts, which King Solomon had made for the house of the Lord\u2014the
        bronze of all these articles was beyond measure. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now concerning the pillars: the height of one pillar was eighteen
        cubits, a measuring line of twelve cubits could measure its circumference,
        and its thickness was four fingers; it  was hollow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'A capital of bronze was on it; and the height of one capital was
        five cubits, with a network and pomegranates all around the capital, all
        of bronze. The second pillar, with pomegranates was the same. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The People Taken Captive to Babylonia'
      title: The People Taken Captive to Babylonia
      number: 23
      content: There were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; all the pomegranates,
        all around on the network, were one hundred.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, Zephaniah
        the second priest, and the three doorkeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He also took out of the city an officer who had charge of the men
        of war, seven men of the king\u2019s close associates who were found in the
        city, the principal scribe of the army who mustered the people of the land,
        and sixty men of the people of the land who were found in the midst of the
        city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took these and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then the king of Babylon struck them and put them to death at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath. Thus Judah was carried away captive from its own land.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These are the people whom Nebuchadnezzar carried away captive: in
        the seventh year, three thousand and twenty-three Jews; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar he carried away captive
        from Jerusalem eight hundred and thirty-two persons; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Jehoiachin Released from Prison'
      title: Jehoiachin Released from Prison
      number: 30
      content: in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuzaradan the captain
        of the guard carried away captive of the Jews seven hundred and forty-five
        persons. All the persons were four thousand six hundred.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now it came to pass in the thirty-seventh year of the captivity of
        Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-fifth day of
        the month, that Evil-Merodach king of Babylon, in the first year of his reign,
        lifted up the head of Jehoiachin king of Judah and brought him out of prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he spoke kindly to him and gave him a more prominent seat than
        those of the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Jehoiachin changed from his prison garments, and he ate bread
        regularly before the king all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And as for his provisions, there was a regular ration given him by
        the king of Babylon, a portion for each day until the day of his death, all
        the days of his life.
      comments: []
